661 /*
662  * Note about ERROR_LIST and INTEGER_LIST type
663  * ERROR_LIST type is an array of bool type with the size of -(ER_LAST_ERROR)
664  * INTEGER_LIST type is an array of int type where the first element is
665  * the size of the array. The max size of INTEGER_LIST is 255.
666  */
667 
668 /*
669  * Bit masks for flag representing status words
670  */
671 
672 /*
673  * Static flags
674  */
675 #define PRM_EMPTY_FLAG 0x00000000 /* empty flag */
676 #define PRM_USER_CHANGE 0x00000001 /* user can change, not implemented */
677 #define PRM_FOR_CLIENT 0x00000002 /* is for client parameter */
678 #define PRM_FOR_SERVER 0x00000004 /* is for server parameter */
679 #define PRM_HIDDEN 0x00000008 /* is hidden */
680 #define PRM_RELOADABLE 0x00000010 /* is reloadable */
681 #define PRM_COMPOUND 0x00000020 /* sets the value of several others */
682 #define PRM_TEST_CHANGE 0x00000040 /* can only be changed in the test mode */
683 #define PRM_FOR_HA 0x00000080 /* is for heartbeat */
684 #define PRM_FOR_SESSION 0x00000100 /* is a session parameter - all client or client/server parameters that can be
685  * changed on-line */
686 #define PRM_FORCE_SERVER 0x00000200 /* client should get value from server */
687 #define PRM_FOR_QRY_STRING 0x00000400 /* if a parameter can affect the plan generation it should be included in the
688  * query string */
689 #define PRM_CLIENT_SESSION 0x00000800 /* mark those client/server session parameters that should not affect the
690  * server */
691 #define PRM_SIZE_UNIT 0x00001000 /* has size unit interface */
692 #define PRM_TIME_UNIT 0x00002000 /* has time unit interface */
693 #define PRM_DIFFER_UNIT 0x00004000 /* parameter unit need to be changed */
694 #define PRM_FOR_HA_CONTEXT 0x00008000 /* should be replicated into HA log applier */
695 
696 #define PRM_GET_SERVER 0x00010000 /* return the value of server parameter from client/server parameter. Note that
697  * this flag only can be set if the parameter has PRM_FOR_CLIENT,
698  * PRM_FOR_SERVER, and PRM_USER_CHANGE flags. */
699 
700 #define PRM_DEPRECATED 0x40000000 /* is deprecated */
701 #define PRM_OBSOLETED 0x80000000 /* is obsoleted */
702 
703 /*
704  * Dynamic flags
705  */
706 #define PRM_SET 0x00000001 /* has been set */
707 #define PRM_ALLOCATED 0x00000002 /* storage has been malloc'd */
708 #define PRM_DEFAULT_USED 0x00000004 /* Default value has been used */
709 #define PRM_DIFFERENT 0x00000008 /* mark those parameters that have values different than their default.
710  * currently used by parameters that should be printed to query string */
711 
712 /*
713  * Macros to get data type
714  */
715 #define PRM_IS_STRING(x) ((x)->datatype == PRM_STRING)
716 #define PRM_IS_INTEGER(x) ((x)->datatype == PRM_INTEGER)
717 #define PRM_IS_FLOAT(x) ((x)->datatype == PRM_FLOAT)
718 #define PRM_IS_BOOLEAN(x) ((x)->datatype == PRM_BOOLEAN)
719 #define PRM_IS_KEYWORD(x) ((x)->datatype == PRM_KEYWORD)
720 #define PRM_IS_INTEGER_LIST(x) ((x)->datatype == PRM_INTEGER_LIST)
721 #define PRM_IS_BIGINT(x) ((x)->datatype == PRM_BIGINT)
722 
723 /*
724  * Macros to access bit fields
725  */
726 
727 #define PRM_USER_CAN_CHANGE(x) (x & PRM_USER_CHANGE)
728 #define PRM_IS_FOR_CLIENT(x) (x & PRM_FOR_CLIENT)
729 #define PRM_IS_FOR_SERVER(x) (x & PRM_FOR_SERVER)
730 #define PRM_IS_HIDDEN(x) (x & PRM_HIDDEN)
731 #define PRM_IS_RELOADABLE(x) (x & PRM_RELOADABLE)
732 #define PRM_IS_COMPOUND(x) (x & PRM_COMPOUND)
733 #define PRM_TEST_CHANGE_ONLY(x) (x & PRM_TEST_CHANGE)
734 #define PRM_IS_FOR_HA(x) (x & PRM_FOR_HA)
735 #define PRM_IS_FOR_SESSION(x) (x & PRM_FOR_SESSION)
736 #define PRM_GET_FROM_SERVER(x) (x & PRM_FORCE_SERVER)
737 #define PRM_IS_FOR_QRY_STRING(x) (x & PRM_FOR_QRY_STRING)
738 #define PRM_CLIENT_SESSION_ONLY(x) (x & PRM_CLIENT_SESSION)
739 #define PRM_HAS_SIZE_UNIT(x) (x & PRM_SIZE_UNIT)
740 #define PRM_HAS_TIME_UNIT(x) (x & PRM_TIME_UNIT)
741 #define PRM_DIFFERENT_UNIT(x) (x & PRM_DIFFER_UNIT)
742 #define PRM_IS_FOR_HA_CONTEXT(x) (x & PRM_FOR_HA_CONTEXT)
743 #define PRM_IS_GET_SERVER(x) (x & PRM_GET_SERVER)
744 #define PRM_IS_DEPRECATED(x) (x & PRM_DEPRECATED)
745 #define PRM_IS_OBSOLETED(x) (x & PRM_OBSOLETED)
746 
747 #define PRM_IS_SET(x) (x & PRM_SET)
748 #define PRM_IS_ALLOCATED(x) (x & PRM_ALLOCATED)
749 #define PRM_DEFAULT_VAL_USED(x) (x & PRM_DEFAULT_USED)
750 #define PRM_IS_DIFFERENT(x) (x & PRM_DIFFERENT)
751 
752 /*
753  * Macros to manipulate bit fields
754  */
755 
756 #define PRM_CLEAR_BIT(this, here) (here &= ~this)
757 #define PRM_SET_BIT(this, here) (here |= this)

762 
763 #define PRM_GET_INT(x) (*((int *) (x)))
764 #define PRM_GET_FLOAT(x) (*((float *) (x)))
765 #define PRM_GET_STRING(x) (*((char **) (x)))
766 #define PRM_GET_BOOL(x) (*((bool *) (x)))
767 #define PRM_GET_INTEGER_LIST(x) (*((int **) (x)))
768 #define PRM_GET_BIGINT(x) (*((UINT64 *) (x)))

771  * Macros to call functions
772  */
773 
774 #define PRM_ADJUST_FOR_SET_BIGINT_TO_INTEGER(prm,out_val,in_val,err) \
775  do \
776  { \
777  assert ((prm) != NULL && (out_val) != NULL && (in_val) != NULL); \
778  assert (sizeof (*(out_val)) == sizeof (int)); \
779  assert (sizeof (*(in_val)) == sizeof (UINT64)); \
780  *(err) = (SYSPRM_ERR) (*((prm)->set_dup)) ((void *) (out_val), PRM_INTEGER, (void *) (in_val), PRM_BIGINT); \
781  } \
782  while (0)
783 
784 #define PRM_ADJUST_FOR_SET_BIGINT_TO_FLOAT(prm,out_val,in_val,err) \
785  do \
786  { \
787  assert ((prm) != NULL && (out_val) != NULL && (in_val) != NULL); \
788  assert (sizeof (*(out_val)) == sizeof (float)); \
789  assert (sizeof (*(in_val)) == sizeof (UINT64)); \
790  *(err) = (SYSPRM_ERR) (*((prm)->set_dup)) ((void *) (out_val), PRM_FLOAT, (void *) (in_val), PRM_BIGINT); \
791  } \
792  while (0)
793

801  } \
802  while (0)

2196 struct sysprm_param
2197 {
2198  PARAM_ID id; /* parameter ID */
2199  const char *name; /* the keyword expected */
2200  unsigned int static_flag; /* bitmask flag representing status words */
2201  SYSPRM_DATATYPE datatype; /* value data type */
2202  unsigned int *dynamic_flag; /* shared by both original and duplicated */
2203  void *default_value; /* address of (pointer to) default value */
2204  void *value; /* address of (pointer to) current value */
2205  void *upper_limit; /* highest allowable value */
2206  void *lower_limit; /* lowest allowable value */
2207  char *force_value; /* address of (pointer to) force value string */
2208  DUP_PRM_FUNC set_dup; /* set duplicated value to original value */
2209  DUP_PRM_FUNC get_dup; /* get duplicated value from original value */
2210 };
2211 typedef struct sysprm_param SYSPRM_PARAM;

5559 
5560 #define GET_PRM(id) (&prm_Def[(id)])
5561 #define GET_PRM_STATIC_FLAG(id) ((GET_PRM (id))->static_flag)
5562 #define GET_PRM_DYNAMIC_FLAG(id) ((GET_PRM (id))->dynamic_flag)
5563 #define GET_PRM_DATATYPE(id) ((GET_PRM (id))->datatype)
5564 
5565 #if defined (CS_MODE)
5566 #define PRM_PRINT_QRY_STRING(id) (PRM_IS_DIFFERENT (*(GET_PRM_DYNAMIC_FLAG (id))) \
5567  && PRM_IS_FOR_QRY_STRING (GET_PRM_STATIC_FLAG (id)))
5568 #else
5569 #define PRM_PRINT_QRY_STRING(id) (PRM_IS_FOR_QRY_STRING (GET_PRM_STATIC_FLAG (id)))
5570 #endif
5571

5573  && PRM_IS_FOR_SERVER (GET_PRM_STATIC_FLAG (id)) \
5574  && !PRM_CLIENT_SESSION_ONLY (GET_PRM_STATIC_FLAG (id)))
5575 
5576 static int num_session_parameters = 0;
5577 #define NUM_SESSION_PRM num_session_parameters
5578

5580 /*
5581  * Session parameters should be cached with the default values or the values
5582  * loaded from cubrid.conf file. When a new client connects to CAS, it should
5583  * reload these parameters (because some may be changed by previous clients)
5584  */
5585 SESSION_PARAM *cached_session_parameters = NULL;
5586 #endif /* CS_MODE */

5588 /*
5589  * Keyword searches do a intl_mbs_ncasecmp(), using the LENGTH OF THE TABLE KEY
5590  * as the limit, so make sure that overlapping keywords are ordered
5591  * correctly. For example, make sure that "yes" precedes "y".
5592  */
5593 
5594 typedef struct keyval KEYVAL;
5595 struct keyval
5596 {
5597  const char *key;
5598  int val;
5599 };

5782  NULL, /* COMPAT_ORACLE */
5783  PRM_NAME_RETURN_NULL_ON_FUNCTION_ERRORS
5784 };

5917 /* conf files that have been loaded */
5918 #define MAX_NUM_OF_PRM_FILES_LOADED 10
5919 static struct
5920 {
5921  char *conf_path;
5922  char *db_name;
5923 } prm_Files_loaded[MAX_NUM_OF_PRM_FILES_LOADED];
5924 
5925 /*
5926  * prm_file_has_been_loaded - Record the file path that has been loaded
5927  * return: none
5928  * conf_path(in): path of the conf file to be recorded
5929  * db_name(in): db name to be recorded
5930  */
5931 static void
5932 prm_file_has_been_loaded (const char *conf_path, const char *db_name)
5933 {
5934  int i;
5935  assert (conf_path != NULL);
5936 
5937  for (i = 0; i < MAX_NUM_OF_PRM_FILES_LOADED; i++)
5938  {
5939  if (prm_Files_loaded[i].conf_path == NULL)
5940  {
5941  prm_Files_loaded[i].conf_path = strdup (conf_path);
5942  prm_Files_loaded[i].db_name = db_name ? strdup (db_name) : NULL;
5943  return;
5944  }
5945  }
5946 }
5947 
5948 
5949 /*
5950  * sysprm_dump_parameters - Print out current system parameters
5951  * return: none
5952  * fp(in):
5953  */
5954 void
5955 sysprm_dump_parameters (FILE * fp)
5956 {
5957  char buf[LINE_MAX];
5958  int i;
5959  const SYSPRM_PARAM *prm;
5960 
5961  fprintf (fp, "#\n# cubrid.conf\n#\n\n");
5962  fprintf (fp, "# system parameters were loaded from the files ([@section])\n");
5963  for (i = 0; i < MAX_NUM_OF_PRM_FILES_LOADED; i++)
5964  {
5965  if (prm_Files_loaded[i].conf_path != NULL)
5966  {
5967  fprintf (fp, "# %s", prm_Files_loaded[i].conf_path);
5968  if (prm_Files_loaded[i].db_name)
5969  {
5970  fprintf (fp, " [@%s]\n", prm_Files_loaded[i].db_name);
5971  }
5972  else
5973  {
5974  fprintf (fp, "\n");
5975  }
5976  }
5977  }
5978 
5979  fprintf (fp, "\n# system parameters\n");
5980  for (i = 0; i < NUM_PRM; i++)
5981  {
5982  prm = &prm_Def[i];
5983  if (PRM_IS_HIDDEN (prm->static_flag) || PRM_IS_OBSOLETED (prm->static_flag))
5984  {
5985  continue;
5986  }
5987  prm_print (prm, buf, LINE_MAX, PRM_PRINT_NAME, PRM_PRINT_CURR_VAL);
5988  fprintf (fp, "%s\n", buf);
5989  }
5990 
5991  return;
5992 }
5993 
5994 /*
5995  * sysprm_set_er_log_file -
5996  * return: void
5997  * base_db_name(in): database name
5998  *
5999  */
6000 void
6001 sysprm_set_er_log_file (const char *db_name)
6002 {
6003  char *s, *base_db_name;
6004  char local_db_name[DB_MAX_IDENTIFIER_LENGTH];
6005  time_t log_time;
6006  struct tm log_tm, *log_tm_p = &log_tm;
6007  char error_log_name[PATH_MAX];
6008  SYSPRM_PARAM *er_log_file;
6009 
6010  if (db_name == NULL)
6011  {
6012  return;
6013  }
6014 
6015  er_log_file = prm_find (PRM_NAME_ER_LOG_FILE, NULL);
6016  if (er_log_file == NULL || PRM_IS_SET (*er_log_file->dynamic_flag))
6017  {
6018  return;
6019  }
6020 
6021  strncpy (local_db_name, db_name, DB_MAX_IDENTIFIER_LENGTH);
6022  s = strchr (local_db_name, '@');
6023  if (s)
6024  {
6025  *s = '\0';
6026  }
6027  base_db_name = basename ((char *) local_db_name);
6028  if (base_db_name == NULL)
6029  {
6030  return;
6031  }
6032 
6033  log_time = time (NULL);
6034  log_tm_p = localtime_r (&log_time, &log_tm);
6035  if (log_tm_p != NULL)
6036  {
6037  snprintf (error_log_name, PATH_MAX - 1, "%s%c%s_%04d%02d%02d_%02d%02d.err", ER_LOG_FILE_DIR, PATH_SEPARATOR,
6038  base_db_name, log_tm_p->tm_year + 1900, log_tm_p->tm_mon + 1, log_tm_p->tm_mday, log_tm_p->tm_hour,
6039  log_tm_p->tm_min);
6040  prm_set (er_log_file, error_log_name, true);
6041  }
6042 }
6043 
6044 /*
6045  * sysprm_load_and_init_internal - Read system parameters from the init files
6046  * return: NO_ERROR or ER_FAILED
6047  * db_name(in): database name
6048  * conf_file(in): config file
6049  * reload(in):
6050  * load_flags(in):
6051  *
6052  * Note: Parameters would be tuned and forced according to the internal rules.
6053  */
6054 static int
6055 sysprm_load_and_init_internal (const char *db_name, const char *conf_file, bool reload, const int load_flags)
6056 {
6057  char *base_db_name = NULL;
6058  char file_being_dealt_with[PATH_MAX];
6059  char local_db_name[DB_MAX_IDENTIFIER_LENGTH];
6060  unsigned int i;
6061  struct stat stat_buf;
6062  int r = NO_ERROR;
6063  char *s;
6064 #if defined (CS_MODE)
6065  SESSION_PARAM *sprm = NULL;
6066  int num_session_prms;
6067 #endif
6068 
6069  if (reload)
6070  {
6071  for (i = 0; i < NUM_PRM; i++)
6072  {
6073  if (PRM_IS_RELOADABLE (prm_Def[i].static_flag))
6074  {
6075  if (prm_set_default (&prm_Def[i]) != PRM_ERR_NO_ERROR)
6076  {
6077  prm_Def[i].value = (void *) NULL;
6078  }
6079  }
6080  }
6081  }
6082 
6083  if (db_name == NULL)
6084  {
6085  /* initialize message catalog at here because there could be a code path that did not call msgcat_init() before */
6086  if (msgcat_init () != NO_ERROR)
6087  {
6088  return ER_FAILED;
6089  }
6090  base_db_name = NULL;
6091  }
6092  else
6093  {
6094  strncpy (local_db_name, db_name, DB_MAX_IDENTIFIER_LENGTH);
6095  s = strchr (local_db_name, '@');
6096  if (s)
6097  {
6098  *s = '\0';
6099  }
6100  base_db_name = basename ((char *) local_db_name);
6101  }
6102 
6103 #if !defined (CS_MODE)
6104  if (base_db_name != NULL && reload == false)
6105  {
6106  sysprm_set_er_log_file (base_db_name);
6107  }
6108 #endif /* !CS_MODE */
6109 
6110  /*
6111  * Read installation configuration file - $CUBRID/conf/cubrid.conf
6112  * or use conf_file if exist
6113  */
6114 
6115  if (conf_file == NULL)
6116  {
6117  /* use environment variable's value if exist */
6118  conf_file = envvar_get ("CONF_FILE");
6119  if (conf_file != NULL && *conf_file == '\0')
6120  {
6121  conf_file = NULL;
6122  }
6123  }
6124 
6125  if (conf_file != NULL)
6126  {
6127  /* use user specified config path and file */
6128  strncpy (file_being_dealt_with, conf_file, sizeof (file_being_dealt_with) - 1);
6129  }
6130  else
6131  {
6132  envvar_confdir_file (file_being_dealt_with, PATH_MAX, sysprm_conf_file_name);
6133  }
6134 
6135  if (stat (file_being_dealt_with, &stat_buf) != 0)
6136  {
6137  fprintf (stderr, msgcat_message (MSGCAT_CATALOG_CUBRID, MSGCAT_SET_PARAMETERS, PRM_ERR_CANT_ACCESS),
6138  file_being_dealt_with, strerror (errno));
6139  }
6140  else
6141  {
6142  r = prm_read_and_parse_ini_file (file_being_dealt_with, base_db_name, reload, load_flags | SYSPRM_IGNORE_HA);
6143  }
6144 
6145  if (r != NO_ERROR)
6146  {
6147  return r;
6148  }
6149 
6150  if (PRM_HA_MODE != HA_MODE_OFF)
6151  {
6152  /* use environment variable's value if exist */
6153  conf_file = envvar_get ("HA_CONF_FILE");
6154  if (conf_file != NULL && conf_file[0] != '\0')
6155  {
6156  strncpy (file_being_dealt_with, conf_file, PATH_MAX);
6157  }
6158  else
6159  {
6160  envvar_confdir_file (file_being_dealt_with, PATH_MAX, sysprm_ha_conf_file_name);
6161  }
6162  if (stat (file_being_dealt_with, &stat_buf) == 0)
6163  {
6164  r = prm_read_and_parse_ini_file (file_being_dealt_with, NULL, reload, load_flags);
6165  }
6166  }
6167 
6168  if (r != NO_ERROR)
6169  {
6170  return r;
6171  }
6172 
6173  /*
6174  * If a parameter is not given, set it by default
6175  */
6176  for (i = 0; i < NUM_PRM; i++)
6177  {
6178  if (!PRM_IS_SET (*prm_Def[i].dynamic_flag) && !PRM_IS_OBSOLETED (prm_Def[i].static_flag))
6179  {
6180  if (prm_set_default (&prm_Def[i]) != PRM_ERR_NO_ERROR)
6181  {
6182  fprintf (stderr, msgcat_message (MSGCAT_CATALOG_CUBRID, MSGCAT_SET_PARAMETERS, PRM_ERR_NO_VALUE),
6183  prm_Def[i].name);
6184  assert (0);
6185  return ER_FAILED;
6186  }
6187  }
6188  }
6189 
6190 #if defined (SA_MODE) || defined (SERVER_MODE)
6191  init_server_timezone_parameter ();
6192 #endif
6193 
6194  /*
6195  * Perform system parameter check and tuning.
6196  */
6197  prm_check_environment ();
6198  prm_tune_parameters ();
6199 #if 0
6200  if (prm_check_parameters () != NO_ERROR)
6201  {
6202  return ER_FAILED;
6203  }
6204 #endif
6205 
6206  /*
6207  * Perform forced system parameter setting.
6208  */
6209  for (i = 0; i < DIM (prm_Def); i++)
6210  {
6211  if (prm_Def[i].force_value)
6212  {
6213  prm_set (&prm_Def[i], prm_Def[i].force_value, false);
6214  }
6215  }
6216 
6217 #if 0
6218  if (envvar_get ("PARAM_DUMP"))
6219  {
6220  sysprm_dump_parameters (stdout);
6221  }
6222 #endif
6223 
6224  intl_Mbs_support = prm_get_bool_value (PRM_ID_INTL_MBS_SUPPORT);
6225 #if !defined (SERVER_MODE)
6226  intl_String_validation = prm_get_bool_value (PRM_ID_INTL_CHECK_INPUT_STRING);
6227 #endif
6228 
6229  /* count the number of session parameters */
6230  num_session_parameters = 0;
6231  for (i = 0; i < NUM_PRM; i++)
6232  {
6233  if (PRM_IS_FOR_SESSION (prm_Def[i].static_flag))
6234  {
6235  num_session_parameters++;
6236  }
6237  }
6238 #if defined (CS_MODE)
6239  /* cache session parameters */
6240  if (cached_session_parameters != NULL)
6241  {
6242  /* free previous cache */
6243  sysprm_free_session_parameters (&cached_session_parameters);
6244  }
6245  cached_session_parameters = sysprm_alloc_session_parameters ();
6246  num_session_prms = 0;
6247  for (i = 0; i < NUM_PRM; i++)
6248  {
6249  if (PRM_IS_FOR_SESSION (prm_Def[i].static_flag))
6250  {
6251  sprm = &cached_session_parameters[num_session_prms++];
6252  sprm->prm_id = (PARAM_ID) i;
6253  sprm->flag = *prm_Def[i].dynamic_flag;
6254  sprm->datatype = prm_Def[i].datatype;
6255  sysprm_set_sysprm_value_from_parameter (&sprm->value, GET_PRM (i));
6256  sysprm_update_session_prm_flag_allocated (sprm);
6257  }
6258  }
6259 #endif /* CS_MODE */
6260 
6261 #if !defined(NDEBUG)
6262  /* verify flags are not incorrect or confusing */
6263  for (i = 0; i < NUM_PRM; i++)
6264  {
6265  int flag = prm_Def[i].static_flag;
6266  if (PRM_IS_FOR_SESSION (flag) && (!PRM_IS_FOR_CLIENT (flag) || !PRM_USER_CAN_CHANGE (flag)))
6267  {
6268  /* session parameters can only be parameters for client that are changeable on-line */
6269  assert (0);
6270  }
6271  if (PRM_IS_FOR_SESSION (flag) && PRM_IS_HIDDEN (flag))
6272  {
6273  /* hidden parameters are not allowed to use PRM_FOR_SESSION flag */
6274  assert (0);
6275  }
6276  if (PRM_CLIENT_SESSION_ONLY (flag) && (!PRM_IS_FOR_SERVER (flag) || !PRM_IS_FOR_SESSION (flag)))
6277  {
6278  /* client session only makes sense if the parameter is for session and for server */
6279  assert (0);
6280  }
6281  if (PRM_USER_CAN_CHANGE (flag) && PRM_TEST_CHANGE_ONLY (flag))
6282  {
6283  /* do not set both parameters: USER_CHANGE: the user can change parameter value on-line TEST_CHANGE: for QA
6284  * only */
6285  assert (0);
6286  }
6287  if (PRM_IS_GET_SERVER (flag) && (PRM_IS_FOR_SESSION (flag) || PRM_IS_HIDDEN (flag)))
6288  {
6289  /* session and hidden parameters are not allowed to use PRM_GET_SERVER flag */
6290  assert (0);
6291  }
6292  if (PRM_IS_GET_SERVER (flag)
6293  && (!PRM_IS_FOR_CLIENT (flag) || !PRM_IS_FOR_SERVER (flag) || !PRM_USER_CAN_CHANGE (flag)))
6294  {
6295  /* Note that PRM_GET_SERVER flag only can be set if the parameter has PRM_FOR_CLIENT, PRM_FOR_SERVER, and
6296  * PRM_USER_CHANGE flags. */
6297  assert (0);
6298  }
6299  }
6300 #endif
6301 
6302  return NO_ERROR;
6303 }
6304 
6305 /*
6306  * sysprm_load_and_init - Read system parameters from the init files
6307  * return: NO_ERROR or ER_FAILED
6308  * db_name(in): database name
6309  * conf_file(in): config file
6310  *
6311  */
6312 int
6313 sysprm_load_and_init (const char *db_name, const char *conf_file, const int load_flags)
6314 {
6315  return sysprm_load_and_init_internal (db_name, conf_file, false, load_flags);
6316 }
6317 
6318 /*
6319  * sysprm_load_and_init_client - Read system parameters from the init files
6320  * (client version)
6321  * return: NO_ERROR or ER_FAILED
6322  * db_name(in): database name
6323  * conf_file(in): config file
6324  *
6325  */
6326 int
6327 sysprm_load_and_init_client (const char *db_name, const char *conf_file)
6328 {
6329  return sysprm_load_and_init_internal (db_name, conf_file, false, SYSPRM_LOAD_ALL);
6330 }
6331 
6332 /*
6333  * sysprm_reload_and_init - Read system parameters from the init files
6334  * return: NO_ERROR or ER_FAILED
6335  * db_name(in): database name
6336  * conf_file(in): config file
6337  *
6338  */
6339 int
6340 sysprm_reload_and_init (const char *db_name, const char *conf_file)
6341 {
6342  return sysprm_load_and_init_internal (db_name, conf_file, true, SYSPRM_LOAD_ALL);
6343 }
6344 
6345 /*
6346  * prm_load_by_section - Set system parameters from a file
6347  * return: void
6348  * ini(in):
6349  * section(in):
6350  * ignore_section(in):
6351  * reload(in):
6352  * file(in):
6353  * load_flags(in):
6354  */
6355 static int
6356 prm_load_by_section (INI_TABLE * ini, const char *section, bool ignore_section, bool reload, const char *file,
6357  const int load_flags)
6358 {
6359  int i, error;
6360  int sec_len;
6361  const char *sec_p;
6362  const char *key, *value;
6363  SYSPRM_PARAM *prm;
6364  bool on_server = false;
6365  bool on_client = false;
6366 
6367 #if defined(SERVER_MODE)
6368  on_server = true;
6369 #endif
6370 
6371 #if defined(CS_MODE)
6372  on_client = true;
6373 #endif
6374 
6375  sec_p = (ignore_section) ? NULL : section;
6376 
6377  for (i = 0; i < ini->size; i++)
6378  {
6379  if (ini->key[i] == NULL || ini->val[i] == NULL)
6380  {
6381  continue;
6382  }
6383 
6384  key = ini->key[i];
6385  value = ini->val[i];
6386 
6387  if (ini_hassec (key))
6388  {
6389  sec_len = ini_seccmp (key, section);
6390  if (!sec_len)
6391  {
6392  continue;
6393  }
6394  sec_len++;
6395  }
6396  else
6397  {
6398  if (ignore_section)
6399  {
6400  sec_len = 1;
6401  }
6402  else
6403  {
6404  continue;
6405  }
6406  }
6407 
6408  prm = prm_find (key + sec_len, sec_p);
6409  if (prm == NULL)
6410  {
6411  error = PRM_ERR_UNKNOWN_PARAM;
6412  prm_report_bad_entry (key + sec_len, ini->lineno[i], error, file);
6413  return error;
6414  }
6415 
6416 #if defined (CS_MODE)
6417  if (PRM_IS_FOR_SERVER (prm->static_flag) && !PRM_IS_FOR_CLIENT (prm->static_flag))
6418  {
6419  /* prm for only server */
6420  continue;
6421  }
6422 #endif /* CS_MODE */
6423 
6424 #if defined (SERVER_MODE)
6425  if (PRM_IS_FOR_CLIENT (prm->static_flag) && !PRM_IS_FOR_SERVER (prm->static_flag))
6426  {
6427  /* prm for only client */
6428  continue;
6429  }
6430 #endif /* SERVER_MODE */
6431 
6432  if (reload && !PRM_IS_RELOADABLE (prm->static_flag))
6433  {
6434  continue;
6435  }
6436  if (!SYSPRM_LOAD_IS_IGNORE_HA (load_flags) && !PRM_IS_FOR_HA (prm->static_flag))
6437  {
6438  continue;
6439  }
6440 
6441  if (PRM_IS_OBSOLETED (prm->static_flag))
6442  {
6443  continue;
6444  }
6445 
6446  if (PRM_IS_DEPRECATED (prm->static_flag))
6447  {
6448  prm_report_bad_entry (key + sec_len, ini->lineno[i], PRM_ERR_DEPRICATED, file);
6449  }
6450 
6451  if (on_server && strcmp (prm->name, PRM_NAME_TIMEZONE) == 0)
6452  {
6453  continue;
6454  }
6455 
6456  if (SYSPRM_LOAD_IS_IGNORE_INTL (load_flags)
6457  && (strcmp (prm->name, PRM_NAME_INTL_DATE_LANG) == 0
6458  || strcmp (prm->name, PRM_NAME_INTL_NUMBER_LANG) == 0
6459  || strcmp (prm->name, PRM_NAME_INTL_CHECK_INPUT_STRING) == 0
6460  || strcmp (prm->name, PRM_NAME_INTL_COLLATION) == 0
6461  || strcmp (prm->name, PRM_NAME_INTL_MBS_SUPPORT) == 0
6462  || strcmp (prm->name, PRM_NAME_SERVER_TIMEZONE) == 0 || strcmp (prm->name, PRM_NAME_TIMEZONE) == 0))
6463  {
6464  continue;
6465  }
6466 
6467  if (strcmp (prm->name, PRM_NAME_SERVER_TIMEZONE) == 0)
6468  {
6469  TZ_REGION tz_region_system;
6470  int er_status = NO_ERROR;
6471 
6472  if (value != NULL)
6473  {
6474  /* offset timezone can work without timezone lib */
6475  er_status = tz_str_to_region (value, strlen (value), &tz_region_system);
6476  if (er_status != NO_ERROR)
6477  {
6478  /* we may have geographic region name, make sure timezone lib is loaded */
6479  if (tz_load () != NO_ERROR)
6480  {
6481  return PRM_ERR_BAD_VALUE;
6482  }
6483  er_status = tz_str_to_region (value, strlen (value), &tz_region_system);
6484  }
6485  if (er_status != NO_ERROR)
6486  {
6487  error = PRM_ERR_BAD_VALUE;
6488  prm_report_bad_entry (key + sec_len, ini->lineno[i], error, file);
6489  return error;
6490  }
6491  tz_set_tz_region_system (&tz_region_system);
6492  }
6493  }
6494 
6495  if ((on_server || on_client)
6496  && (strcmp (prm->name, PRM_NAME_SERVER_TIMEZONE) == 0 || strcmp (prm->name, PRM_NAME_TIMEZONE) == 0))
6497  {
6498  int er_status = NO_ERROR;
6499 
6500  if (value != NULL)
6501  {
6502  /* offset timezone can work without timezone lib */
6503 #if !defined(SERVER_MODE)
6504  er_status = tz_str_to_region (value, strlen (value), tz_get_client_tz_region_session ());
6505 #else
6506  er_status = tz_str_to_region (value, strlen (value), NULL);
6507 #endif
6508  if (er_status != NO_ERROR)
6509  {
6510  /* we may have geographic region name, make sure timezone lib is loaded */
6511  if (tz_load () != NO_ERROR)
6512  {
6513  return PRM_ERR_BAD_VALUE;
6514  }
6515 #if !defined(SERVER_MODE)
6516  er_status = tz_str_to_region (value, strlen (value), tz_get_client_tz_region_session ());
6517 #else
6518  er_status = tz_str_to_region (value, strlen (value), NULL);
6519 #endif
6520  }
6521  if (er_status != NO_ERROR)
6522  {
6523  error = PRM_ERR_BAD_VALUE;
6524  prm_report_bad_entry (key + sec_len, ini->lineno[i], error, file);
6525  return error;
6526  }
6527  }
6528  }
6529 
6530  error = prm_set (prm, value, true);
6531  if (error != NO_ERROR)
6532  {
6533  prm_report_bad_entry (key + sec_len, ini->lineno[i], error, file);
6534  return error;
6535  }
6536  }
6537 
6538  return NO_ERROR;
6539 }
6540 
6541 /*
6542  * prm_read_and_parse_ini_file - Set system parameters from a file
6543  * return: NO_ERROR or error code defined in enum SYSPRM_ERR
6544  * prm_file_name(in):
6545  * db_name(in):
6546  * reload(in):
6547  * load_flags(in):
6548  */
6549 static int
6550 prm_read_and_parse_ini_file (const char *prm_file_name, const char *db_name, const bool reload, const int load_flags)
6551 {
6552  INI_TABLE *ini;
6553  char sec_name[LINE_MAX];
6554  char host_name[MAXHOSTNAMELEN];
6555  char user_name[MAXHOSTNAMELEN];
6556  int error;
6557 
6558  ini = ini_parser_load (prm_file_name);
6559  if (ini == NULL)
6560  {
6561  fprintf (stderr, msgcat_message (MSGCAT_CATALOG_CUBRID, MSGCAT_SET_PARAMETERS, PRM_ERR_CANT_OPEN_INIT),
6562  prm_file_name, strerror (errno));
6563  return PRM_ERR_FILE_ERR;
6564  }
6565 
6566  error = prm_load_by_section (ini, "common", true, reload, prm_file_name, load_flags);
6567  if (error == NO_ERROR && SYSPRM_LOAD_IS_IGNORE_HA (load_flags) && db_name != NULL && *db_name != '\0')
6568  {
6569  snprintf (sec_name, LINE_MAX, "@%s", db_name);
6570  error = prm_load_by_section (ini, sec_name, true, reload, prm_file_name, load_flags);
6571  }
6572 
6573 #if defined (SA_MODE)
6574  if (error == NO_ERROR)
6575  {
6576  error = prm_load_by_section (ini, "standalone", true, reload, prm_file_name, load_flags);
6577  }
6578 #endif /* SA_MODE */
6579 
6580  if (error == NO_ERROR && SYSPRM_LOAD_IS_IGNORE_HA (load_flags))
6581  {
6582  error = prm_load_by_section (ini, "service", false, reload, prm_file_name, load_flags);
6583  }
6584  if (error == NO_ERROR && !SYSPRM_LOAD_IS_IGNORE_HA (load_flags) && PRM_HA_MODE != HA_MODE_OFF
6585  && GETHOSTNAME (host_name, MAXHOSTNAMELEN) == 0)
6586  {
6587  snprintf (sec_name, LINE_MAX, "%%%s|*", host_name);
6588  error = prm_load_by_section (ini, sec_name, true, reload, prm_file_name, load_flags);
6589  if (error == NO_ERROR && getlogin_r (user_name, MAXHOSTNAMELEN) == 0)
6590  {
6591  snprintf (sec_name, LINE_MAX, "%%%s|%s", host_name, user_name);
6592  error = prm_load_by_section (ini, sec_name, true, reload, prm_file_name, load_flags);
6593  }
6594  }
6595 
6596  ini_parser_free (ini);
6597 
6598  prm_file_has_been_loaded (prm_file_name, db_name);
6599 
6600  return error;
6601 }
6602 
6603 /*
6604  * prm_size_to_io_pages -
6605  * return: value
6606  */
6607 static int
6608 prm_size_to_io_pages (void *out_val, SYSPRM_DATATYPE out_type, void *in_val, SYSPRM_DATATYPE in_type)
6609 {
6610  if (out_val == NULL || in_val == NULL)
6611  {
6612  return PRM_ERR_BAD_VALUE;
6613  }
6614 
6615  if (out_type == PRM_INTEGER && in_type == PRM_BIGINT)
6616  {
6617  int *page_value = (int *) out_val;
6618  UINT64 *size_value = (UINT64 *) in_val;
6619  UINT64 tmp_value;
6620 
6621  tmp_value = *size_value / IO_PAGESIZE;
6622  if (*size_value % IO_PAGESIZE > 0)
6623  {
6624  tmp_value++;
6625  }
6626 
6627  if (tmp_value > INT_MAX)
6628  {
6629  return PRM_ERR_BAD_RANGE;
6630  }
6631  else
6632  {
6633  *page_value = (int) tmp_value;
6634  }
6635  }
6636  else if (out_type == PRM_FLOAT && in_type == PRM_BIGINT)
6637  {
6638  float *page_value = (float *) out_val;
6639  UINT64 *size_value = (UINT64 *) in_val;
6640  double tmp_value;
6641 
6642  tmp_value = (double) *size_value / IO_PAGESIZE;
6643 
6644  if (tmp_value > FLT_MAX)
6645  {
6646  return PRM_ERR_BAD_RANGE;
6647  }
6648  else
6649  {
6650  *page_value = ceilf ((float) tmp_value * 100) / 100;
6651  }
6652  }
6653  else
6654  {
6655  assert_release (false);
6656  return PRM_ERR_BAD_VALUE;
6657  }
6658 
6659  return NO_ERROR;
6660 }

6676  UINT64 *size_value = (UINT64 *) out_val;
6677  UINT64 page_value = *(int *) in_val;
6678 
6679  *size_value = (UINT64) (page_value * IO_PAGESIZE);
6680  }
6681  else if (out_type == PRM_BIGINT && in_type == PRM_FLOAT)
6682  {
6683  UINT64 *size_value = (UINT64 *) out_val;
6684  float page_value = *(float *) in_val;
6685 
6686  *size_value = (UINT64) (page_value * IO_PAGESIZE);
6687  }
6688  else
6689  {
6690  assert_release (false);
6691  return PRM_ERR_BAD_VALUE;
6692  }
6693 
6694  return NO_ERROR;

6945 /*
6946  * prm_equal_to_ori -

6948  */
6949 static int
6950 prm_equal_to_ori (void *out_val, SYSPRM_DATATYPE out_type, void *in_val, SYSPRM_DATATYPE in_type)
6951 {

6954  return PRM_ERR_BAD_VALUE;
6955  }
6956 
6957  if (out_type == PRM_INTEGER && in_type == PRM_INTEGER)
6958  {
6959  int *in_value = (int *) in_val;
6960  int *out_value = (int *) out_val;
6961 
6962  *out_value = *in_value;
6963  }
6964  else if (out_type == PRM_FLOAT && in_type == PRM_FLOAT)
6965  {
6966  float *in_value = (float *) in_val;
6967  float *out_value = (float *) out_val;
6968 
6969  *out_value = *in_value;
6970  }
6971  else if (out_type == PRM_BIGINT && in_type == PRM_BIGINT)
6972  {
6973  UINT64 *in_value = (UINT64 *) in_val;
6974  UINT64 *out_value = (UINT64 *) out_val;
6975 
6976  *out_value = *in_value;
6977  }
6978  else if (out_type == PRM_INTEGER && in_type == PRM_BIGINT)
6979  {
6980  UINT64 *in_value = (UINT64 *) in_val;
6981  int *out_value = (int *) out_val;
6982 
6983  if (*in_value > INT_MAX)
6984  {
6985  return PRM_ERR_BAD_RANGE;
6986  }
6987 
6988  *out_value = (int) *in_value;
6989  }
6990  else if (out_type == PRM_BIGINT && in_type == PRM_INTEGER)
6991  {
6992  int *in_value = (int *) in_val;
6993  UINT64 *out_value = (UINT64 *) out_val;
6994 
6995  *out_value = (UINT64) (*in_value);
6996  }
6997  else
6998  {
6999  assert_release (false);
7000  return PRM_ERR_BAD_VALUE;
7001  }
7002 
7003  return NO_ERROR;
