7006 /*
7007  * prm_check_parameters -
7008  * return: int
7009  */
7010 static int
7011 prm_check_parameters (void)
7012 {
7013  /*
7014  * ha_node_list and ha_db_list should be not null for ha_mode=yes|replica
7015  */
7016  if (PRM_HA_MODE != HA_MODE_OFF)
7017  {
7018  if (PRM_HA_NODE_LIST == NULL || PRM_HA_NODE_LIST[0] == 0 || PRM_HA_DB_LIST == NULL || PRM_HA_DB_LIST[0] == 0)
7019  {
7020  fprintf (stderr, msgcat_message (MSGCAT_CATALOG_CUBRID, MSGCAT_SET_PARAMETERS, PRM_ERR_NO_VALUE),
7021  PRM_NAME_HA_NODE_LIST);
7022  return ER_FAILED;
7023  }
7024  }
7025 
7026  return NO_ERROR;
7027 }
7028 
7029 /*
7030  * prm_check_environment -
7031  * return: none
7032  */
7033 static void
7034 prm_check_environment (void)
7035 {
7036  int i;
7037  char buf[PRM_DEFAULT_BUFFER_SIZE];
7038 
7039  for (i = 0; i < NUM_PRM; i++)
7040  {
7041  SYSPRM_PARAM *prm;
7042  const char *str;
7043 
7044  prm = &prm_Def[i];
7045  strncpy (buf, prm->name, sizeof (buf) - 1);
7046  buf[sizeof (buf) - 1] = '\0';
7047  ustr_upper (buf);
7048 
7049  str = envvar_get (buf);
7050  if (str && str[0])
7051  {
7052  int error;
7053  error = prm_set (prm, str, true);
7054  if (error != 0)
7055  {
7056  prm_report_bad_entry (prm->name, -1, error, buf);
7057  }
7058  }
7059  }
7060 }
7061 
7062 /*
7063  * sysprm_validate_escape_char_parameters () - validate escape char setting
7064  *
7065  * return : SYSPRM_ERR
7066  * assignments_list (in) : list of assignments to validate.
7067  *
7068  * NOTE: To validate whether there will be conflictive settings between
7069  * PRM_ID_REQUIRE_LIKE_ESCAPE_CHARACTER and PRM_ID_NO_BACKSLASH_ESCAPES.
7070  * Since both must not simultaneously be true.
7071  */
7072 static SYSPRM_ERR
7073 sysprm_validate_escape_char_parameters (const SYSPRM_ASSIGN_VALUE * assignment_list)
7074 {
7075  SYSPRM_PARAM *prm = NULL;
7076  const SYSPRM_ASSIGN_VALUE *assignment = NULL;
7077  bool set_require_like_escape, set_no_backslash_escape;
7078  bool is_require_like_escape, is_no_backslash_escape;
7079 
7080  set_require_like_escape = set_no_backslash_escape = false;
7081  for (assignment = assignment_list; assignment != NULL; assignment = assignment->next)
7082  {
7083  if (assignment->prm_id == PRM_ID_REQUIRE_LIKE_ESCAPE_CHARACTER)
7084  {
7085  set_require_like_escape = true;
7086  is_require_like_escape = assignment->value.b;
7087  }
7088  else if (assignment->prm_id == PRM_ID_NO_BACKSLASH_ESCAPES)
7089  {
7090  set_no_backslash_escape = true;
7091  is_no_backslash_escape = assignment->value.b;
7092  }
7093  }
7094 
7095  if (!set_require_like_escape && !set_no_backslash_escape)
7096  {
7097  return PRM_ERR_NO_ERROR;
7098  }
7099 
7100  if (!set_no_backslash_escape)
7101  {
7102  prm = GET_PRM (PRM_ID_NO_BACKSLASH_ESCAPES);
7103  is_no_backslash_escape = PRM_GET_BOOL (prm->value);
7104  }
7105 
7106  if (!set_require_like_escape)
7107  {
7108  prm = GET_PRM (PRM_ID_REQUIRE_LIKE_ESCAPE_CHARACTER);
7109  is_require_like_escape = PRM_GET_BOOL (prm->value);
7110  }
7111 
7112  if (is_require_like_escape == true && is_no_backslash_escape == true)
7113  {
7114  return PRM_ERR_CANNOT_CHANGE;
7115  }
7116 
7117  return PRM_ERR_NO_ERROR;
7118 }
7119 
7120 #if !defined (SERVER_MODE)
7121 /*
7122  * sysprm_validate_change_parameters () - validate the parameter value changes
7123  *
7124  * return : SYSPRM_ERR
7125  * data (in) : string containing "parameter = value" assignments
7126  * check (in) : check if user can change parameter and if
7127  * parameter should also change on server. set to
7128  * false if assignments are supposed to be forced and
7129  * not checked.
7130  * assignments_ptr (out) : list of assignments.
7131  *
7132  * NOTE: Data string is parsed entirely and if all changes are valid a list
7133  * of SYSPRM_ASSIGN_VALUEs is generated. If any change is invalid an
7134  * error is returned and no list is generated.
7135  * If changes need to be done on server too PRM_ERR_NOT_FOR_CLIENT or
7136  * PRM_ERR_NOT_FOR_CLIENT_NO_AUTH is returned.
7137  */
7138 SYSPRM_ERR
7139 sysprm_validate_change_parameters (const char *data, bool check, SYSPRM_ASSIGN_VALUE ** assignments_ptr)
7140 {
7141  char buf[LINE_MAX], *p = NULL, *name = NULL, *value = NULL;
7142  SYSPRM_PARAM *prm = NULL;
7143  SYSPRM_ERR err = PRM_ERR_NO_ERROR;
7144  SYSPRM_ASSIGN_VALUE *assignments = NULL, *last_assign = NULL;
7145  SYSPRM_ERR change_error = PRM_ERR_NO_ERROR;
7146 
7147  assert (assignments_ptr != NULL);
7148  *assignments_ptr = NULL;
7149 
7150  if (!data || *data == '\0')
7151  {
7152  return PRM_ERR_BAD_VALUE;
7153  }
7154 
7155  if (intl_mbs_ncpy (buf, data, sizeof (buf)) == NULL)
7156  {
7157  return PRM_ERR_BAD_VALUE;
7158  }
7159 
7160  p = buf;
7161  do
7162  {
7163  /* parse data */
7164  SYSPRM_ASSIGN_VALUE *assign = NULL;
7165 
7166  /* get parameter name and value */
7167  err = (SYSPRM_ERR) prm_get_next_param_value (&p, &name, &value);
7168  if (err != PRM_ERR_NO_ERROR || name == NULL || value == NULL)
7169  {
7170  break;
7171  }
7172 
7173  prm = prm_find (name, NULL);
7174  if (prm == NULL)
7175  {
7176  err = PRM_ERR_UNKNOWN_PARAM;
7177  break;
7178  }
7179 
7180  if (!check || PRM_USER_CAN_CHANGE (prm->static_flag)
7181  || (PRM_TEST_CHANGE_ONLY (prm->static_flag) && PRM_TEST_MODE))
7182  {
7183  /* We allow changing the parameter value. */
7184  }
7185  else
7186  {
7187  err = PRM_ERR_CANNOT_CHANGE;
7188  break;
7189  }
7190 
7191  /* create a SYSPRM_CHANGE_VAL object */
7192  assign = (SYSPRM_ASSIGN_VALUE *) malloc (sizeof (SYSPRM_ASSIGN_VALUE));
7193  if (assign == NULL)
7194  {
7195  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, sizeof (SYSPRM_ASSIGN_VALUE));
7196  err = PRM_ERR_NO_MEM_FOR_PRM;
7197  break;
7198  }
7199  err = sysprm_generate_new_value (prm, value, check, &assign->value);
7200  if (err != PRM_ERR_NO_ERROR)
7201  {
7202  if (err == PRM_ERR_NOT_FOR_CLIENT || err == PRM_ERR_NOT_FOR_CLIENT_NO_AUTH)
7203  {
7204  /* update change_error */
7205  if (change_error != PRM_ERR_NOT_FOR_CLIENT || err != PRM_ERR_NOT_FOR_CLIENT_NO_AUTH)
7206  {
7207  /* do not replace change_error PRM_ERR_NOT_FOR_CLIENT with PRM_ERR_NOT_FOR_CLIENT_NO_AUTH */
7208  change_error = err;
7209  }
7210  /* do not invalidate assignments */
7211  err = PRM_ERR_NO_ERROR;
7212  }
7213  else
7214  {
7215  /* bad value */
7216  free_and_init (assign);
7217  break;
7218  }
7219  }
7220  assign->prm_id = sysprm_get_id (prm);
7221  assign->next = NULL;
7222 
7223  /* append to assignments list */
7224  if (assignments != NULL)
7225  {
7226  last_assign->next = assign;
7227  last_assign = assign;
7228  }
7229  else
7230  {
7231  assignments = last_assign = assign;
7232  }
7233  }
7234  while (p);
7235 
7236  if (err == PRM_ERR_NO_ERROR)
7237  {
7238  err = sysprm_validate_escape_char_parameters (assignments);
7239  }
7240 
7241  if (err == PRM_ERR_NO_ERROR)
7242  {
7243  /* changes are valid, save assignments list */
7244  *assignments_ptr = assignments;
7245 
7246  /* return change_error in order to update values on server too */
7247  return change_error;
7248  }
7249 
7250  /* changes are not valid, clean up */
7251  sysprm_free_assign_values (&assignments);
7252  return err;
7253 }
7254 
7255 /*
7256  * sysprm_make_default_values () -
7257  *
7258  * return : SYSPRM_ERR
7259  * data (in) : string containing "parameter = value" assignments
7260  * default_val_buf(out) : string containing "parameter = def_value"
7261  * assignments created from data argument
7262  * buf_size(in) : size available in default_val_buf
7263  *
7264  */
7265 SYSPRM_ERR
7266 sysprm_make_default_values (const char *data, char *default_val_buf, const int buf_size)
7267 {
7268  char buf[LINE_MAX], *p = NULL, *out_p = NULL;
7269  char *name = NULL, *value = NULL;
7270  int remaining_size, n;
7271  SYSPRM_ERR err = PRM_ERR_NO_ERROR;
7272  SYSPRM_PARAM *prm = NULL;
7273 
7274  if (intl_mbs_ncpy (buf, data, sizeof (buf)) == NULL)
7275  {
7276  return PRM_ERR_BAD_VALUE;
7277  }
7278 
7279  p = buf;
7280  out_p = default_val_buf;
7281  remaining_size = buf_size - 1;
7282  do
7283  {
7284  /* get parameter name and value */
7285  err = (SYSPRM_ERR) prm_get_next_param_value (&p, &name, &value);
7286  if (err != PRM_ERR_NO_ERROR || name == NULL || value == NULL)
7287  {
7288  break;
7289  }
7290 
7291  prm = prm_find (name, NULL);
7292  if (prm == NULL)
7293  {
7294  err = PRM_ERR_UNKNOWN_PARAM;
7295  break;
7296  }
7297 
7298  if (PRM_ID_INTL_COLLATION == sysprm_get_id (prm))
7299  {
7300  n = snprintf (out_p, remaining_size, "%s=%s", PRM_NAME_INTL_COLLATION,
7301  lang_get_collation_name (LANG_GET_BINARY_COLLATION (LANG_SYS_CODESET)));
7302  }
7303  else if (PRM_ID_INTL_DATE_LANG == sysprm_get_id (prm))
7304  {
7305  n = snprintf (out_p, remaining_size, "%s=%s", PRM_NAME_INTL_DATE_LANG, lang_get_Lang_name ());
7306  }
7307  else if (PRM_ID_INTL_NUMBER_LANG == sysprm_get_id (prm))
7308  {
7309  n = snprintf (out_p, remaining_size, "%s=%s", PRM_NAME_INTL_NUMBER_LANG, lang_get_Lang_name ());
7310  }
7311  else if (PRM_ID_TIMEZONE == sysprm_get_id (prm))
7312  {
7313  n = snprintf (out_p, remaining_size, "%s=%s", PRM_NAME_TIMEZONE, tz_get_system_timezone ());
7314  }
7315  else
7316  {
7317  n = prm_print (prm, out_p, remaining_size, PRM_PRINT_NAME, PRM_PRINT_DEFAULT_VAL);
7318  }
7319 
7320  out_p += n;
7321  remaining_size -= n;
7322 
7323  n = snprintf (out_p, remaining_size, ";");
7324  out_p += n;
7325  remaining_size -= n;
7326  }
7327  while (p && remaining_size > 0);
7328 
7329  return err;
7330 }
7331 #endif /* !SERVER_MODE */
7332 
7333 /*
7334  * sysprm_change_parameter_values () - update system parameter values
7335  *
7336  * return : void
7337  * assignments (in) : list of assignments
7338  * check (in) : check if the parameter belongs to current scope
7339  * set_flag (in) : update PRM_SET flag if true
7340  *
7341  * NOTE: This function does not check if the new values are valid (e.g. in
7342  * the restricted range). First validate new values before calling this
7343  * function.
7344  */
7345 void
7346 sysprm_change_parameter_values (const SYSPRM_ASSIGN_VALUE * assignments, bool check, bool set_flag)
7347 {
7348  SYSPRM_PARAM *prm = NULL;
7349  for (; assignments != NULL; assignments = assignments->next)
7350  {
7351  prm = GET_PRM (assignments->prm_id);
7352 #if defined (CS_MODE)
7353  if (check)
7354  {
7355  if (!PRM_IS_FOR_CLIENT (prm->static_flag))
7356  {
7357  /* skip this assignment */
7358  continue;
7359  }
7360  }
7361 #endif
7362 #if defined (SERVER_MODE)
7363  if (check)
7364  {
7365  if (!PRM_IS_FOR_SERVER (prm->static_flag) && !PRM_IS_FOR_SESSION (prm->static_flag))
7366  {
7367  /* skip this assignment */
7368  continue;
7369  }
7370  }
7371 #endif
7372  sysprm_set_value (prm, assignments->value, set_flag, true);
7373 #if defined (SERVER_MODE)
7374  if (sysprm_get_id (prm) == PRM_ID_ACCESS_IP_CONTROL)
7375  {
7376  css_set_accessible_ip_info ();
7377  }
7378 #endif
7379  }
7380 }
7381 
7382 /*
7383  * prm_print - Print a parameter to the buffer
7384  * return: number of chars printed
7385  * prm(in): parameter
7386  * buf(out): print buffer
7387  * len(in): length of the buffer
7388  * print_mode(in): print name/id or just value of the parameter
7389  */
7390 static int
7391 prm_print (const SYSPRM_PARAM * prm, char *buf, size_t len, PRM_PRINT_MODE print_mode,
7392  PRM_PRINT_VALUE_MODE print_value_mode)
7393 {
7394  int n = 0;
7395  PARAM_ID id;
7396  int error = NO_ERROR;
7397  char left_side[PRM_DEFAULT_BUFFER_SIZE];
7398  void *prm_value;
7399 
7400  if (len == 0)
7401  {
7402  /* don't print anything */
7403  return 0;
7404  }
7405 
7406  memset (left_side, 0, PRM_DEFAULT_BUFFER_SIZE);
7407 
7408  assert (prm != NULL && buf != NULL && len > 0);
7409 
7410  if (PRM_DIFFERENT_UNIT (prm->static_flag))
7411  {
7412  assert (prm->get_dup != NULL);
7413  }
7414 
7415  if (print_mode == PRM_PRINT_ID)
7416  {
7417  id = sysprm_get_id (prm);
7418  snprintf (left_side, PRM_DEFAULT_BUFFER_SIZE, "%d=", id);
7419  }
7420  else if (print_mode == PRM_PRINT_NAME)
7421  {
7422  snprintf (left_side, PRM_DEFAULT_BUFFER_SIZE, "%s=", prm->name);
7423  }
7424 
7425  if (print_value_mode == PRM_PRINT_DEFAULT_VAL)
7426  {
7427  prm_value = prm->default_value;
7428  }
7429  else
7430  {
7431  prm_value = prm->value;
7432  }
7433 
7434  if (PRM_IS_INTEGER (prm))
7435  {
7436  int val = PRM_GET_INT (prm_value);
7437  int left_side_len = strlen (left_side);
7438 
7439  if (PRM_DIFFERENT_UNIT (prm->static_flag) && !PRM_HAS_SIZE_UNIT (prm->static_flag)
7440  && !PRM_HAS_TIME_UNIT (prm->static_flag))
7441  {
7442  PRM_ADJUST_FOR_GET_INTEGER_TO_INTEGER (prm, &val, &val, &error);
7443  if (error != NO_ERROR)
7444  {
7445  assert_release (false);
7446  return n;
7447  }
7448  }
7449 
7450  if (PRM_HAS_SIZE_UNIT (prm->static_flag))
7451  {
7452  UINT64 dup_val;
7453  val = PRM_GET_INT (prm_value);
7454 
7455  if (PRM_DIFFERENT_UNIT (prm->static_flag))
7456  {
7457  PRM_ADJUST_FOR_GET_INTEGER_TO_BIGINT (prm, &dup_val, &val, &error);
7458  if (error != NO_ERROR)
7459  {
7460  assert_release (false);
7461  return n;
7462  }
7463  }
7464  else
7465  {
7466  assert_release (false);
7467  }
7468 
7469  (void) util_byte_to_size_string (left_side + left_side_len, PRM_DEFAULT_BUFFER_SIZE - left_side_len, dup_val);
7470  n = snprintf (buf, len, "%s", left_side);
7471  }
7472  else if (PRM_HAS_TIME_UNIT (prm->static_flag))
7473  {
7474  INT64 dup_val;
7475  val = PRM_GET_INT (prm_value);
7476 
7477  if (PRM_DIFFERENT_UNIT (prm->static_flag) && val >= 0)
7478  {
7479  UINT64 tmp_val;
7480  PRM_ADJUST_FOR_GET_INTEGER_TO_BIGINT (prm, &tmp_val, &val, &error);
7481  if (error != NO_ERROR)
7482  {
7483  assert_release (false);
7484  return n;
7485  }
7486  dup_val = (INT64) tmp_val;
7487  }
7488  else
7489  {
7490  dup_val = (INT64) val;
7491  }
7492 
7493  (void) util_msec_to_time_string (left_side + left_side_len, PRM_DEFAULT_BUFFER_SIZE - left_side_len, dup_val);
7494  n = snprintf (buf, len, "%s", left_side);
7495  }
7496  else
7497  {
7498  n = snprintf (buf, len, "%s%d", left_side, val);
7499  }
7500  }
7501  else if (PRM_IS_BIGINT (prm))
7502  {
7503  UINT64 val = PRM_GET_BIGINT (prm_value);
7504  int left_side_len = strlen (left_side);
7505 
7506  if (PRM_DIFFERENT_UNIT (prm->static_flag))
7507  {
7508  PRM_ADJUST_FOR_GET_BIGINT_TO_BIGINT (prm, &val, &val, &error);
7509  if (error != NO_ERROR)
7510  {
7511  assert_release (false);
7512  return n;
7513  }
7514  }
7515 
7516  if (PRM_HAS_SIZE_UNIT (prm->static_flag))
7517  {
7518  (void) util_byte_to_size_string (left_side + left_side_len, PRM_DEFAULT_BUFFER_SIZE - left_side_len, val);
7519  n = snprintf (buf, len, "%s", left_side);
7520  }
7521  else
7522  {
7523  n = snprintf (buf, len, "%s%lld", left_side, (unsigned long long) val);
7524  }
7525  }
7526  else if (PRM_IS_BOOLEAN (prm))
7527  {
7528  n = snprintf (buf, len, "%s%c", left_side, (PRM_GET_BOOL (prm_value) ? 'y' : 'n'));
7529  }
7530  else if (PRM_IS_FLOAT (prm))
7531  {
7532  float val = PRM_GET_FLOAT (prm_value);
7533  int left_side_len = strlen (left_side);
7534 
7535  if (PRM_DIFFERENT_UNIT (prm->static_flag) && !PRM_HAS_SIZE_UNIT (prm->static_flag))
7536  {
7537  PRM_ADJUST_FOR_GET_FLOAT_TO_FLOAT (prm, &val, &val, &error);
7538  if (error != NO_ERROR)
7539  {
7540  assert_release (false);
7541  return n;
7542  }
7543  }
7544 
7545  if (PRM_HAS_SIZE_UNIT (prm->static_flag))
7546  {
7547  UINT64 dup_val;
7548  val = PRM_GET_FLOAT (prm_value);
7549 
7550  if (PRM_DIFFERENT_UNIT (prm->static_flag))
7551  {
7552  PRM_ADJUST_FOR_GET_FLOAT_TO_BIGINT (prm, &dup_val, &val, &error);
7553  if (error != NO_ERROR)
7554  {
7555  assert_release (false);
7556  return n;
7557  }
7558  }
7559  else
7560  {
7561  assert_release (false);
7562  }
7563 
7564  (void) util_byte_to_size_string (left_side + left_side_len, PRM_DEFAULT_BUFFER_SIZE - left_side_len, dup_val);
7565  n = snprintf (buf, len, "%s", left_side);
7566  }
7567  else
7568  {
7569  n = snprintf (buf, len, "%s%f", left_side, val);
7570  }
7571  }
7572  else if (PRM_IS_STRING (prm))
7573  {
7574  n = snprintf (buf, len, "%s\"%s\"", left_side, (PRM_GET_STRING (prm_value) ? PRM_GET_STRING (prm_value) : ""));
7575  }
7576  else if (PRM_IS_KEYWORD (prm))
7577  {
7578  const KEYVAL *keyvalp = NULL;
7579 
7580  if (intl_mbs_casecmp (prm->name, PRM_NAME_ER_LOG_LEVEL) == 0)
7581  {
7582  keyvalp = prm_keyword (PRM_GET_INT (prm_value), NULL, er_log_level_words, DIM (er_log_level_words));
7583  }
7584  else if (intl_mbs_casecmp (prm->name, PRM_NAME_LOG_ISOLATION_LEVEL) == 0)
7585  {
7586  keyvalp = prm_keyword (PRM_GET_INT (prm_value), NULL, isolation_level_words, DIM (isolation_level_words));
7587  }
7588  else if (intl_mbs_casecmp (prm->name, PRM_NAME_PB_DEBUG_PAGE_VALIDATION_LEVEL) == 0)
7589  {
7590  keyvalp =
7591  prm_keyword (PRM_GET_INT (prm_value), NULL, pgbuf_debug_page_validation_level_words,
7592  DIM (pgbuf_debug_page_validation_level_words));
7593  }
7594  else if (intl_mbs_casecmp (prm->name, PRM_NAME_HA_MODE) == 0
7595  || intl_mbs_casecmp (prm->name, PRM_NAME_HA_MODE_FOR_SA_UTILS_ONLY) == 0)
7596 
7597  {
7598  keyvalp = prm_keyword (PRM_GET_INT (prm_value), NULL, ha_mode_words, DIM (ha_mode_words));
7599  }
7600  else if (intl_mbs_casecmp (prm->name, PRM_NAME_HA_SERVER_STATE) == 0)
7601  {
7602  keyvalp = prm_keyword (PRM_GET_INT (prm_value), NULL, ha_server_state_words, DIM (ha_server_state_words));
7603  }
7604  else if (intl_mbs_casecmp (prm->name, PRM_NAME_HA_LOG_APPLIER_STATE) == 0)
7605  {
7606  keyvalp =
7607  prm_keyword (PRM_GET_INT (prm_value), NULL, ha_log_applier_state_words, DIM (ha_log_applier_state_words));
7608  }
7609  else if (intl_mbs_casecmp (prm->name, PRM_NAME_COMPAT_MODE) == 0)
7610  {
7611  keyvalp = prm_keyword (PRM_GET_INT (prm_value), NULL, compat_words, DIM (compat_words));
7612  }
7613  else if (intl_mbs_casecmp (prm->name, PRM_NAME_CHECK_PEER_ALIVE) == 0)
7614  {
7615  keyvalp = prm_keyword (PRM_GET_INT (prm_value), NULL, check_peer_alive_words, DIM (check_peer_alive_words));
7616  }
7617  else if (intl_mbs_casecmp (prm->name, PRM_NAME_QUERY_TRACE_FORMAT) == 0)
7618  {
7619  keyvalp =
7620  prm_keyword (PRM_GET_INT (prm_value), NULL, query_trace_format_words, DIM (query_trace_format_words));
7621  }
7622  else if (intl_mbs_casecmp (prm->name, PRM_NAME_FAULT_INJECTION_TEST) == 0)
7623  {
7624  keyvalp = prm_keyword (PRM_GET_INT (prm_value), NULL, fi_test_words, DIM (fi_test_words));
7625  }
7626  else if (intl_mbs_casecmp (prm->name, PRM_NAME_HA_REPL_FILTER_TYPE) == 0)
7627  {
7628  keyvalp =
7629  prm_keyword (PRM_GET_INT (prm->value), NULL, ha_repl_filter_type_words, DIM (ha_repl_filter_type_words));
7630  }
7631  else
7632  {
7633  assert (false);
7634  }
7635 
7636  if (keyvalp)
7637  {
7638  n = snprintf (buf, len, "%s\"%s\"", left_side, keyvalp->key);
7639  }
7640  else
7641  {
7642  n = snprintf (buf, len, "%s%d", left_side, PRM_GET_INT (prm_value));
7643  }
7644  }
7645  else if (PRM_IS_INTEGER_LIST (prm))
7646  {
7647  int *int_list, list_size, i;
7648  char *s;
7649 
7650  int_list = PRM_GET_INTEGER_LIST (prm_value);
7651  if (int_list)
7652  {
7653  list_size = int_list[0];
7654  s = buf;
7655  n = snprintf (s, len, "%s", left_side);
7656  s += n;
7657  len -= n;
7658 
7659  for (i = 1; i <= list_size; i++)
7660  {
7661  n = snprintf (s, len, "%d,", int_list[i]);
7662  s += n;
7663  len -= n;
7664  }
7665 
7666  if (list_size > 0)
7667  {
7668  /* remove last "," */
7669  s -= 1;
7670  len += 1;
7671  }
7672  if (len > 0)
7673  {
7674  *s = '\0';
7675  }
7676  n = strlen (buf);
7677  }
7678  else
7679  {
7680  n = snprintf (buf, len, "%s", left_side);
7681  }
7682  }
7683  else
7684  {
7685  n = snprintf (buf, len, "%s?", left_side);
7686  }
7687 
7688  return n;
7689 }
7690 
7691 /*
7692  * sysprm_print_sysprm_value () - print sysprm_value
7693  *
7694  * return : length of printed string
7695  * prm_id (in) : parameter ID (to which sysprm_value belongs).
7696  * value (in) : printed sysprm_value
7697  * buf (in/out) : printing destination
7698  * len (in) : maximum size of printed string
7699  * print_mode (in) : PRM_PRINT_MODE
7700  */
7701 static int
7702 sysprm_print_sysprm_value (PARAM_ID prm_id, SYSPRM_VALUE value, char *buf, size_t len, PRM_PRINT_MODE print_mode)
7703 {
7704  int n = 0;
7705  int error = NO_ERROR;
7706  char left_side[PRM_DEFAULT_BUFFER_SIZE];
7707  SYSPRM_PARAM *prm = NULL;
7708 
7709  if (len == 0)
7710  {
7711  /* don't print anything */
7712  return 0;
7713  }
7714 
7715  memset (left_side, 0, PRM_DEFAULT_BUFFER_SIZE);
7716 
7717  assert (buf != NULL && len > 0);
7718  prm = GET_PRM (prm_id);
7719 
7720  if (PRM_DIFFERENT_UNIT (prm->static_flag))
7721  {
7722  assert (prm->get_dup != NULL);
7723  }
7724 
7725  if (print_mode == PRM_PRINT_ID)
7726  {
7727  snprintf (left_side, PRM_DEFAULT_BUFFER_SIZE, "%d=", prm_id);
7728  }
7729  else if (print_mode == PRM_PRINT_NAME)
7730  {
7731  snprintf (left_side, PRM_DEFAULT_BUFFER_SIZE, "%s=", prm->name);
7732  }
7733 
7734  if (PRM_IS_INTEGER (prm))
7735  {
7736  int val = value.i;
7737  int left_side_len = strlen (left_side);
7738 
7739  if (PRM_DIFFERENT_UNIT (prm->static_flag) && !PRM_HAS_SIZE_UNIT (prm->static_flag)
7740  && !PRM_HAS_TIME_UNIT (prm->static_flag))
7741  {
7742  PRM_ADJUST_FOR_GET_INTEGER_TO_INTEGER (prm, &val, &val, &error);
7743  if (error != NO_ERROR)
7744  {
7745  assert_release (false);
7746  return n;
7747  }
7748  }
7749 
7750  if (PRM_HAS_SIZE_UNIT (prm->static_flag))
7751  {
7752  UINT64 dup_val;
7753  val = value.i;
7754 
7755  if (PRM_DIFFERENT_UNIT (prm->static_flag))
7756  {
7757  PRM_ADJUST_FOR_GET_INTEGER_TO_BIGINT (prm, &dup_val, &val, &error);
7758  if (error != NO_ERROR)
7759  {
7760  assert_release (false);
7761  return n;
7762  }
7763  }
7764  else
7765  {
7766  assert_release (false);
7767  }
7768 
7769  (void) util_byte_to_size_string (left_side + left_side_len, PRM_DEFAULT_BUFFER_SIZE - left_side_len, dup_val);
7770  n = snprintf (buf, len, "%s", left_side);
7771  }
7772  else if (PRM_HAS_TIME_UNIT (prm->static_flag))
7773  {
7774  INT64 dup_val;
7775  val = value.i;
7776 
7777  if (PRM_DIFFERENT_UNIT (prm->static_flag) && val >= 0)
7778  {
7779  UINT64 tmp_val;
7780  PRM_ADJUST_FOR_GET_INTEGER_TO_BIGINT (prm, &tmp_val, &val, &error);
7781  if (error != NO_ERROR)
7782  {
7783  assert_release (false);
7784  return n;
7785  }
7786  dup_val = (INT64) tmp_val;
7787  }
7788  else
7789  {
7790  dup_val = (INT64) val;
7791  }
7792 
7793  (void) util_msec_to_time_string (left_side + left_side_len, PRM_DEFAULT_BUFFER_SIZE - left_side_len, dup_val);
7794  n = snprintf (buf, len, "%s", left_side);
7795  }
7796  else
7797  {
7798  n = snprintf (buf, len, "%s%d", left_side, val);
7799  }
7800  }
7801  else if (PRM_IS_BIGINT (prm))
7802  {
7803  UINT64 val = value.bi;
7804  int left_side_len = strlen (left_side);
7805 
7806  if (PRM_DIFFERENT_UNIT (prm->static_flag))
7807  {
7808  PRM_ADJUST_FOR_GET_BIGINT_TO_BIGINT (prm, &val, &val, &error);
7809  if (error != NO_ERROR)
7810  {
7811  assert_release (false);
7812  return n;
7813  }
7814  }
7815 
7816  if (PRM_HAS_SIZE_UNIT (prm->static_flag))
7817  {
7818  (void) util_byte_to_size_string (left_side + left_side_len, PRM_DEFAULT_BUFFER_SIZE - left_side_len, val);
7819  n = snprintf (buf, len, "%s", left_side);
7820  }
7821  else
7822  {
7823  n = snprintf (buf, len, "%s%lld", left_side, (unsigned long long) val);
7824  }
7825  }
7826  else if (PRM_IS_BOOLEAN (prm))
7827  {
7828  n = snprintf (buf, len, "%s%c", left_side, (value.b ? 'y' : 'n'));
7829  }
7830  else if (PRM_IS_FLOAT (prm))
7831  {
7832  float val = value.f;
7833  int left_side_len = strlen (left_side);
7834 
7835  if (PRM_DIFFERENT_UNIT (prm->static_flag) && !PRM_HAS_SIZE_UNIT (prm->static_flag))
7836  {
7837  PRM_ADJUST_FOR_GET_FLOAT_TO_FLOAT (prm, &val, &val, &error);
7838  if (error != NO_ERROR)
7839  {
7840  assert_release (false);
7841  return n;
7842  }
7843  }
7844 
7845  if (PRM_HAS_SIZE_UNIT (prm->static_flag))
7846  {
7847  UINT64 dup_val;
7848  val = value.f;
7849 
7850  if (PRM_DIFFERENT_UNIT (prm->static_flag))
7851  {
7852  PRM_ADJUST_FOR_GET_FLOAT_TO_BIGINT (prm, &dup_val, &val, &error);
7853  if (error != NO_ERROR)
7854  {
7855  assert_release (false);
7856  return n;
7857  }
7858  }
7859  else
7860  {
7861  assert_release (false);
7862  }
7863 
7864  (void) util_byte_to_size_string (left_side + left_side_len, PRM_DEFAULT_BUFFER_SIZE - left_side_len, dup_val);
7865  n = snprintf (buf, len, "%s", left_side);
7866  }
7867  else
7868  {
7869  n = snprintf (buf, len, "%s%f", left_side, val);
7870  }
7871  }
7872  else if (PRM_IS_STRING (prm))
7873  {
7874  n = snprintf (buf, len, "%s\"%s\"", left_side, (value.str != NULL ? value.str : ""));
7875  }
7876  else if (PRM_IS_KEYWORD (prm))
7877  {
7878  const KEYVAL *keyvalp = NULL;
7879 
7880  if (intl_mbs_casecmp (prm->name, PRM_NAME_ER_LOG_LEVEL) == 0)
7881  {
7882  keyvalp = prm_keyword (value.i, NULL, er_log_level_words, DIM (er_log_level_words));
7883  }
7884  else if (intl_mbs_casecmp (prm->name, PRM_NAME_LOG_ISOLATION_LEVEL) == 0)
7885  {
7886  keyvalp = prm_keyword (value.i, NULL, isolation_level_words, DIM (isolation_level_words));
7887  }
7888  else if (intl_mbs_casecmp (prm->name, PRM_NAME_PB_DEBUG_PAGE_VALIDATION_LEVEL) == 0)
7889  {
7890  keyvalp =
7891  prm_keyword (value.i, NULL, pgbuf_debug_page_validation_level_words,
7892  DIM (pgbuf_debug_page_validation_level_words));
7893  }
7894  else if (intl_mbs_casecmp (prm->name, PRM_NAME_HA_MODE) == 0
7895  || intl_mbs_casecmp (prm->name, PRM_NAME_HA_MODE_FOR_SA_UTILS_ONLY) == 0)
7896  {
7897  keyvalp = prm_keyword (value.i, NULL, ha_mode_words, DIM (ha_mode_words));
7898  }
7899  else if (intl_mbs_casecmp (prm->name, PRM_NAME_HA_SERVER_STATE) == 0)
7900  {
7901  keyvalp = prm_keyword (value.i, NULL, ha_server_state_words, DIM (ha_server_state_words));
7902  }
7903  else if (intl_mbs_casecmp (prm->name, PRM_NAME_HA_LOG_APPLIER_STATE) == 0)
7904  {
7905  keyvalp = prm_keyword (value.i, NULL, ha_log_applier_state_words, DIM (ha_log_applier_state_words));
7906  }
7907  else if (intl_mbs_casecmp (prm->name, PRM_NAME_COMPAT_MODE) == 0)
7908  {
7909  keyvalp = prm_keyword (value.i, NULL, compat_words, DIM (compat_words));
7910  }
7911  else if (intl_mbs_casecmp (prm->name, PRM_NAME_CHECK_PEER_ALIVE) == 0)
7912  {
7913  keyvalp = prm_keyword (value.i, NULL, check_peer_alive_words, DIM (check_peer_alive_words));
7914  }
7915  else if (intl_mbs_casecmp (prm->name, PRM_NAME_QUERY_TRACE_FORMAT) == 0)
7916  {
7917  keyvalp = prm_keyword (value.i, NULL, query_trace_format_words, DIM (query_trace_format_words));
7918  }
7919  else if (intl_mbs_casecmp (prm->name, PRM_NAME_FAULT_INJECTION_TEST) == 0)
7920  {
7921  keyvalp = prm_keyword (value.i, NULL, fi_test_words, DIM (fi_test_words));
7922  }
7923  else if (intl_mbs_casecmp (prm->name, PRM_NAME_HA_REPL_FILTER_TYPE) == 0)
7924  {
7925  keyvalp = prm_keyword (value.i, NULL, ha_repl_filter_type_words, DIM (ha_repl_filter_type_words));
7926  }
7927  else
7928  {
7929  assert (false);
7930  }
7931 
7932  if (keyvalp)
7933  {
7934  n = snprintf (buf, len, "%s\"%s\"", left_side, keyvalp->key);
7935  }
7936  else
7937  {
7938  n = snprintf (buf, len, "%s%d", left_side, value.i);
7939  }
7940  }
7941  else if (PRM_IS_INTEGER_LIST (prm))
7942  {
7943  int *int_list = NULL, list_size, i;
7944  char *s = NULL;
7945 
7946  int_list = value.integer_list;
7947  if (int_list)
7948  {
7949  list_size = int_list[0];
7950  s = buf;
7951  n = snprintf (s, len, "%s", left_side);
7952  s += n;
7953  len -= n;
7954 
7955  for (i = 1; i <= list_size; i++)
7956  {
7957  n = snprintf (s, len, "%d,", int_list[i]);
7958  s += n;
7959  len -= n;
7960  }
7961 
7962  if (list_size > 0)
7963  {
7964  /* remove last "," */
7965  s -= 1;
7966  len += 1;
7967  }
7968  if (len > 0)
7969  {
7970  *s = '\0';
7971  }
7972  n = strlen (buf);
7973  }
7974  else
7975  {
7976  n = snprintf (buf, len, "%s", left_side);
7977  }
7978  }
7979  else
7980  {
7981  n = snprintf (buf, len, "%s?", left_side);
7982  }
7983 
7984  return n;
7985 }
7986 
7987 /*
7988  * sysprm_obtain_parameters () - Get parameter values
7989  *
7990  * return : SYSPRM_ERR code.
7991  * data (in) : string containing the names of parameters.
7992  * prm_values_ptr (out) : list of ids and values for the parameters read from
7993  * data.
7994  *
7995  * NOTE: Multiple parameters can be obtained by providing a string like:
7996  * "param_name1; param_name2; ..."
7997  * If some values must be read from server, PRM_ERR_NOT_FOR_CLIENT is
7998  * returned.
7999  */
8000 SYSPRM_ERR
8001 sysprm_obtain_parameters (char *data, SYSPRM_ASSIGN_VALUE ** prm_values_ptr)
8002 {
8003  char buf[LINE_MAX], *p = NULL, *name = NULL;
8004  SYSPRM_PARAM *prm = NULL;
8005  SYSPRM_ASSIGN_VALUE *prm_value_list = NULL, *last_prm_value = NULL;
8006  SYSPRM_ASSIGN_VALUE *prm_value = NULL;
8007  SYSPRM_ERR error = PRM_ERR_NO_ERROR, scope_error = PRM_ERR_NO_ERROR;
8008 
8009  if (!data || *data == '\0')
8010  {
8011  return PRM_ERR_BAD_VALUE;
8012  }
8013 
8014  if (intl_mbs_ncpy (buf, data, LINE_MAX) == NULL)
8015  {
8016  return PRM_ERR_BAD_VALUE;
8017  }
8018 
8019  assert (prm_values_ptr != NULL);
8020  *prm_values_ptr = NULL;
8021 
8022  p = buf;
8023  do
8024  {
8025  /* read name */
8026  while (char_isspace (*p))
8027  {
8028  p++;
8029  }
8030  if (*p == '\0')
8031  {
8032  break;
8033  }
8034  name = p;
8035 
8036  while (*p && !char_isspace (*p) && *p != ';')
8037  {
8038  p++;
8039  }
8040 
8041  if (*p)
8042  {
8043  *p++ = '\0';
8044  while (char_isspace (*p))
8045  {
8046  p++;
8047  }
8048  if (*p == ';')
8049  {
8050  p++;
8051  }
8052  }
8053 
8054  prm = prm_find (name, NULL);
8055  if (prm == NULL)
8056  {
8057  error = PRM_ERR_UNKNOWN_PARAM;
8058  break;
8059  }
8060 
8061 #if defined (CS_MODE)
8062  if (!PRM_IS_FOR_CLIENT (prm->static_flag) && !PRM_IS_FOR_SERVER (prm->static_flag))
8063  {
8064  error = PRM_ERR_CANNOT_CHANGE;
8065  break;
8066  }
8067 
8068  if ((PRM_IS_FOR_SERVER (prm->static_flag) && !PRM_IS_FOR_CLIENT (prm->static_flag))
8069  || PRM_IS_GET_SERVER (prm->static_flag))
8070  {
8071  /* have to read the value on server */
8072  scope_error = PRM_ERR_NOT_FOR_CLIENT;
8073  }
8074 #endif /* CS_MODE */
8075 
8076  /* create a SYSPRM_ASSING_VALUE object to store parameter value */
8077  prm_value = (SYSPRM_ASSIGN_VALUE *) malloc (sizeof (SYSPRM_ASSIGN_VALUE));
8078  if (prm_value == NULL)
8079  {
8080  error = PRM_ERR_NO_MEM_FOR_PRM;
8081  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, sizeof (SYSPRM_ASSIGN_VALUE));
8082  break;
8083  }
8084  prm_value->prm_id = sysprm_get_id (prm);
8085  prm_value->next = NULL;
8086 #if defined (CS_MODE)
8087  if (PRM_IS_FOR_CLIENT (prm->static_flag))
8088  {
8089  /* set the value here */
8090  sysprm_set_sysprm_value_from_parameter (&prm_value->value, prm);
8091  }
8092  else
8093  {
8094  memset (&prm_value->value, 0, sizeof (SYSPRM_VALUE));
8095  }
8096 #else /* CS_MODE */
8097  sysprm_set_sysprm_value_from_parameter (&prm_value->value, prm);
8098 #endif /* !CS_MODE */
8099 
8100  /* append prm_value to prm_value_list */
8101  if (prm_value_list != NULL)
8102  {
8103  last_prm_value->next = prm_value;
8104  last_prm_value = prm_value;
8105  }
8106  else
8107  {
8108  prm_value_list = last_prm_value = prm_value;
8109  }
8110  }
8111  while (*p);
8112 
8113  if (error == PRM_ERR_NO_ERROR)
8114  {
8115  /* all parameter names are valid and values can be obtained */
8116  *prm_values_ptr = prm_value_list;
8117  /* update error in order to get values from server too if needed */
8118  error = scope_error;
8119  }
8120  else
8121  {
8122  /* error obtaining values, clean up */
8123  sysprm_free_assign_values (&prm_value_list);
8124  }
8125 
8126  return error;
8127 }
8128 
8129 #if !defined(CS_MODE)
8130 /*
8131  * xsysprm_change_server_parameters () - changes parameter values on server
8132  *
8133  * return : void
8134  * assignments (in) : list of changes
8135  */
8136 void
8137 xsysprm_change_server_parameters (const SYSPRM_ASSIGN_VALUE * assignments)
8138 {
8139  sysprm_change_parameter_values (assignments, true, true);
8140 }
8141 
8142 /*
8143  * xsysprm_obtain_server_parameters () - get parameter values from server
8144  *
8145  * return : void
8146  * prm_values (in) : list of parameters
8147  *
8148  * NOTE: Obtains value for parameters that are for server only. For parameters
8149  * that are client/server, values should be obtained from client UNLESS
8150  * it has PRM_GET_SERVER flag.
8151  */
8152 void
8153 xsysprm_obtain_server_parameters (SYSPRM_ASSIGN_VALUE * prm_values)
8154 {
8155  SYSPRM_PARAM *prm = NULL;
8156 
8157  for (; prm_values != NULL; prm_values = prm_values->next)
8158  {
8159  prm = GET_PRM (prm_values->prm_id);
8160 
8161  if ((PRM_IS_FOR_SERVER (prm->static_flag) && !PRM_IS_FOR_CLIENT (prm->static_flag))
8162  || PRM_IS_GET_SERVER (prm->static_flag))
8163  {
8164  /* set value */
8165  sysprm_set_sysprm_value_from_parameter (&prm_values->value, prm);
8166  }
8167  }
8168 }
8169 
8170 /*
8171  * xsysprm_get_force_server_parameters () - obtain values for parameters
8172  * marked as PRM_FORCE_SERVER
8173  *
8174  * return : list of values
8175  *
8176  * NOTE: This is called after client registers to server.
8177  */
8178 SYSPRM_ASSIGN_VALUE *
8179 xsysprm_get_force_server_parameters (void)
8180 {
8181  SYSPRM_ASSIGN_VALUE *force_values = NULL, *last_assign = NULL;
8182  SYSPRM_PARAM *prm = NULL;
8183  int i;
8184 
8185  for (i = 0; i < NUM_PRM; i++)
8186  {
8187  prm = GET_PRM (i);
8188  if (PRM_GET_FROM_SERVER (prm->static_flag))
8189  {
8190  SYSPRM_ASSIGN_VALUE *change_val = (SYSPRM_ASSIGN_VALUE *) malloc (sizeof (SYSPRM_ASSIGN_VALUE));
8191  if (change_val == NULL)
8192  {
8193  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, sizeof (SYSPRM_ASSIGN_VALUE));
8194  goto cleanup;
8195  }
8196  change_val->prm_id = (PARAM_ID) i;
8197  change_val->next = NULL;
8198  sysprm_set_sysprm_value_from_parameter (&change_val->value, prm);
8199  if (force_values != NULL)
8200  {
8201  last_assign->next = change_val;
8202  last_assign = change_val;
8203  }
8204  else
8205  {
8206  force_values = last_assign = change_val;
8207  }
8208  }
8209  }
8210 
8211  return force_values;
8212 
8213 cleanup:
8214  sysprm_free_assign_values (&force_values);
8215  return NULL;
8216 }
8217 
8218 /*
8219  * xsysprm_dump_server_parameters -
8220  * return: none
8221  * fp(in):
8222  */
8223 void
8224 xsysprm_dump_server_parameters (FILE * outfp)
8225 {
8226  sysprm_dump_parameters (outfp);
8227 }
8228 #endif /* !CS_MODE */
8229 
8230 /*
8231  * sysprm_get_param_range - returns the minimum and maximum value for a SYSPRM_PARAM
8232  * return: error code
8233  * prm (in): the parameter for which we want the limits
8234  * min (out): the minimum possible value for the parameter
8235  * max (out): the maximum possible value for the parameter
8236  */
8237 static SYSPRM_ERR
8238 sysprm_get_param_range (SYSPRM_PARAM * prm, void *min, void *max)
8239 {
8240  SYSPRM_ERR error = PRM_ERR_NO_ERROR;
8241  if (PRM_IS_INTEGER (prm))
8242  {
8243  if (prm->lower_limit)
8244  {
8245  *((int *) min) = PRM_GET_INT (prm->lower_limit);
8246  if (PRM_DIFFERENT_UNIT (prm->static_flag))
8247  {
8248  PRM_ADJUST_FOR_GET_INTEGER_TO_INTEGER (prm, (int *) min, (int *) min, &error);
8249  }
8250  }
8251  else
8252  {
8253  *((int *) min) = INT_MIN;
8254  }
8255 
8256  if (prm->upper_limit)
8257  {
8258  *((int *) max) = PRM_GET_INT (prm->upper_limit);
8259  if (PRM_DIFFERENT_UNIT (prm->static_flag))
8260  {
8261  PRM_ADJUST_FOR_GET_INTEGER_TO_INTEGER (prm, (int *) max, (int *) max, &error);
8262  }
8263  }
8264  else
8265  {
8266  *((int *) max) = INT_MAX;
8267  }
8268  }
8269  else if (PRM_IS_FLOAT (prm))
8270  {
8271  if (prm->lower_limit)
8272  {
8273  *((float *) min) = PRM_GET_FLOAT (prm->lower_limit);
8274  if (PRM_DIFFERENT_UNIT (prm->static_flag))
8275  {
8276  PRM_ADJUST_FOR_GET_FLOAT_TO_FLOAT (prm, (float *) min, (float *) min, &error);
8277  }
8278  }
8279  else
8280  {
8281  *((float *) min) = FLT_MIN;
8282  }
8283 
8284  if (prm->upper_limit)
8285  {
8286  *((float *) max) = PRM_GET_FLOAT (prm->upper_limit);
8287  if (PRM_DIFFERENT_UNIT (prm->static_flag))
8288  {
8289  PRM_ADJUST_FOR_GET_FLOAT_TO_FLOAT (prm, (float *) max, (float *) max, &error);
8290  }
8291  }
8292  else
8293  {
8294  *((float *) max) = FLT_MAX;
8295  }
8296  }
8297  else if (PRM_IS_BIGINT (prm))
8298  {
8299  if (prm->lower_limit)
8300  {
8301  *((UINT64 *) min) = PRM_GET_BIGINT (prm->lower_limit);
8302  if (PRM_DIFFERENT_UNIT (prm->static_flag))
8303  {
8304  PRM_ADJUST_FOR_GET_BIGINT_TO_BIGINT (prm, (UINT64 *) min, (UINT64 *) min, &error);
8305  }
8306  }
8307  else
8308  {
8309  *((UINT64 *) min) = 0ULL;
8310  }
8311 
8312  if (prm->upper_limit)
8313  {
8314  *((UINT64 *) max) = PRM_GET_BIGINT (prm->upper_limit);
8315  if (PRM_DIFFERENT_UNIT (prm->static_flag))
8316  {
8317  PRM_ADJUST_FOR_GET_BIGINT_TO_BIGINT (prm, (UINT64 *) max, (UINT64 *) max, &error);
8318  }
8319  }
8320  else
8321  {
8322  *((UINT64 *) max) = ULLONG_MAX;
8323  }
8324  }
8325  else
8326  {
8327  return PRM_ERR_BAD_VALUE;
8328  }
8329 
8330  if (error != NO_ERROR)
8331  {
8332  return PRM_ERR_BAD_VALUE;
8333  }
8334 
8335  return PRM_ERR_NO_ERROR;
8336 }
8337 
8338 /*
8339  * sysprm_get_range - returns the minimum and maximum value
8340  * for a paramter, given by its name
8341  * return: error code
8342  * pname (in): parameter name
8343  * min (out): the minimum possible value for the parameter
8344  * max (out): the maximum possible value for the parameter
8345  */
8346 int
8347 sysprm_get_range (const char *pname, void *min, void *max)
8348 {
8349  SYSPRM_PARAM *prm;
8350 
8351  prm = prm_find (pname, NULL);
8352  if (prm == NULL)
8353  {
8354  return PRM_ERR_UNKNOWN_PARAM;
8355  }
8356 
8357  if (PRM_DIFFERENT_UNIT (prm->static_flag))
8358  {
8359  assert (prm->get_dup != NULL);
8360  }
8361  return sysprm_get_param_range (prm, min, max);
8362 }
8363 
8364 /*
8365  * sysprm_check_range -
8366  * return:
8367  * pname (in): parameter name
8368  * value (in): parameter value
8369  */
8370 int
8371 sysprm_check_range (const char *pname, void *value)
8372 {
8373  int error = 0;
8374  SYSPRM_PARAM *prm;
8375 
8376  prm = prm_find (pname, NULL);
8377  if (prm == NULL)
8378  {
8379  return PRM_ERR_UNKNOWN_PARAM;
8380  }
8381 
8382  error = prm_check_range (prm, value);
8383 
8384  return error;
8385 }
8386 
8387 /*
8388  * prm_check_range -
8389  * return:
8390  * prm(in):
8391  * value (in):
8392  */
8393 static int
8394 prm_check_range (SYSPRM_PARAM * prm, void *value)
8395 {
8396  int error = NO_ERROR;
8397 
8398  if (PRM_DIFFERENT_UNIT (prm->static_flag))
8399  {
8400  assert (prm->set_dup != NULL);
8401  }
8402 
8403  if (PRM_IS_INTEGER (prm) || PRM_IS_KEYWORD (prm))
8404  {
8405  int val;
8406 
8407  if (PRM_DIFFERENT_UNIT (prm->static_flag))
8408  {
8409  if (PRM_HAS_SIZE_UNIT (prm->static_flag))
8410  {
8411  PRM_ADJUST_FOR_SET_BIGINT_TO_INTEGER (prm, &val, (UINT64 *) value, &error);
8412  }
8413  else if (PRM_HAS_TIME_UNIT (prm->static_flag))
8414  {
8415  INT64 *dup_val = (INT64 *) value;
8416 
8417  if (*dup_val >= 0)
8418  {
8419  UINT64 tmp_val = (UINT64) * dup_val;
8420  PRM_ADJUST_FOR_SET_BIGINT_TO_INTEGER (prm, &val, &tmp_val, &error);
8421  }
8422  else
8423  {
8424  val = (int) *dup_val;
8425  }
8426  }
8427  else
8428  {
8429  PRM_ADJUST_FOR_SET_INTEGER_TO_INTEGER (prm, &val, (int *) value, &error);
8430  }
8431  if (error != NO_ERROR)
8432  {
8433  return PRM_ERR_BAD_VALUE;
8434  }
8435  }
8436  else
8437  {
8438  val = *((int *) value);
8439  }
8440 
8441  if ((prm->upper_limit && PRM_GET_INT (prm->upper_limit) < val)
8442  || (prm->lower_limit && PRM_GET_INT (prm->lower_limit) > val))
8443  {
8444  return PRM_ERR_BAD_RANGE;
8445  }
8446  }
8447  else if (PRM_IS_FLOAT (prm))
8448  {
8449  float val;
8450  float lower, upper;
8451 
8452  lower = upper = 0; /* to make compilers be silent */
8453  if (PRM_DIFFERENT_UNIT (prm->static_flag))
8454  {
8455  if (PRM_HAS_SIZE_UNIT (prm->static_flag))
8456  {
8457  PRM_ADJUST_FOR_SET_BIGINT_TO_FLOAT (prm, &val, (UINT64 *) value, &error);
8458  }
8459  else
8460  {
8461  PRM_ADJUST_FOR_SET_FLOAT_TO_FLOAT (prm, &val, (float *) value, &error);
8462  }
8463  if (error != NO_ERROR)
8464  {
8465  return PRM_ERR_BAD_VALUE;
8466  }
8467 
8468  if (prm->upper_limit)
8469  {
8470  upper = ceilf (PRM_GET_FLOAT (prm->upper_limit) * 100) / 100;
8471  }
8472 
8473  if (prm->lower_limit)
8474  {
8475  lower = ceilf (PRM_GET_FLOAT (prm->lower_limit) * 100) / 100;
8476  }
8477  }
8478  else
8479  {
8480  val = *((float *) value);
8481 
8482  if (prm->upper_limit)
8483  {
8484  upper = PRM_GET_FLOAT (prm->upper_limit);
8485  }
8486 
8487  if (prm->lower_limit)
8488  {
8489  lower = PRM_GET_FLOAT (prm->lower_limit);
8490  }
8491  }
8492 
8493  if ((prm->upper_limit && upper < val) || (prm->lower_limit && lower > val))
8494  {
8495  return PRM_ERR_BAD_RANGE;
8496  }
8497  }
8498  else if (PRM_IS_BIGINT (prm))
8499  {
8500  UINT64 val;
8501 
8502  if (PRM_DIFFERENT_UNIT (prm->static_flag))
8503  {
8504  PRM_ADJUST_FOR_SET_BIGINT_TO_BIGINT (prm, &val, (UINT64 *) value, &error);
8505  if (error != NO_ERROR)
8506  {
8507  return PRM_ERR_BAD_VALUE;
8508  }
8509  }
8510  else
8511  {
8512  val = *((UINT64 *) value);
8513  }
8514 
8515  if ((prm->upper_limit && PRM_GET_BIGINT (prm->upper_limit) < val)
8516  || (prm->lower_limit && PRM_GET_BIGINT (prm->lower_limit) > val))
8517  {
8518  return PRM_ERR_BAD_RANGE;
8519  }
8520  }
8521  else
8522  {
8523  return PRM_ERR_BAD_VALUE;
8524  }
8525 
8526  return PRM_ERR_NO_ERROR;
8527 }
8528 
8529 /*
8530  * sysprm_generate_new_value () - converts string into a system parameter value
8531  *
8532  * return : SYSPRM_ERR
8533  * prm (in) : target system parameter
8534  * value (in) : parameter value in char * format
8535  * check (in) : check if value can be changed. set to false if value
8536  * should be forced
8537  * new_value (out) : SYSPRM_VALUE converted from string
8538  */
8539 static SYSPRM_ERR
8540 sysprm_generate_new_value (SYSPRM_PARAM * prm, const char *value, bool check, SYSPRM_VALUE * new_value)
8541 {
8542  char *end = NULL;
8543  int error = NO_ERROR;
8544  int set_min = 0, set_max = 0, set_default = 0;
8545  SYSPRM_ERR ret = PRM_ERR_NO_ERROR;
8546  SYSPRM_VALUE min, max;
8547 
8548  if (prm == NULL)
8549  {
8550  return PRM_ERR_UNKNOWN_PARAM;
8551  }
8552  if (value == NULL)
8553  {
8554  return PRM_ERR_BAD_VALUE;
8555  }
8556 
8557  assert (new_value != NULL);
8558 
8559  if (PRM_DIFFERENT_UNIT (prm->static_flag))
8560  {
8561  assert (prm->set_dup != NULL);
8562  }
8563 
8564 #if defined (CS_MODE)
8565  if (check)
8566  {
8567  /* check the scope of parameter */
8568  if (PRM_IS_FOR_CLIENT (prm->static_flag))
8569  {
8570  if (PRM_IS_FOR_SESSION (prm->static_flag))
8571  {
8572  /* the value in session state must also be updated. user doesn't have to be part of DBA group. */
8573  ret = PRM_ERR_NOT_FOR_CLIENT_NO_AUTH;
8574  }
8575  else if (PRM_IS_FOR_SERVER (prm->static_flag))
8576  {
8577  /* the value has to be changed on server too. user has to be part of DBA group. */
8578  ret = PRM_ERR_NOT_FOR_CLIENT;
8579  }
8580  }
8581  else
8582  {
8583  if (PRM_IS_FOR_SERVER (prm->static_flag))
8584  {
8585  /* this value is only for server. user has to be DBA. */
8586  ret = PRM_ERR_NOT_FOR_CLIENT;
8587  }
8588  else
8589  {
8590  /* not for client or server, cannot be changed on-line */
8591  return PRM_ERR_CANNOT_CHANGE;
8592  }
8593  }
8594  }
8595 #endif /* CS_MODE */
8596 
8597 #if defined (SERVER_MODE)
8598  if (check)
8599  {
8600  if (!PRM_IS_FOR_SERVER (prm->static_flag) && !PRM_IS_FOR_SESSION (prm->static_flag))
8601  {
8602  return PRM_ERR_NOT_FOR_SERVER;
8603  }
8604  }
8605 #endif /* SERVER_MODE */
8606 
8607  if (strcasecmp (value, PRM_VALUE_DEFAULT) == 0)
8608  {
8609  set_default = true;
8610  }
8611  if (strcasecmp (value, PRM_VALUE_MAX) == 0)
8612  {
8613  set_max = true;
8614  }
8615  if (strcasecmp (value, PRM_VALUE_MIN) == 0)
8616  {
8617  set_min = true;
8618  }
8619 #if defined(CS_MODE)
8620  if (!set_default)
8621  {
8622  if (strcmp (prm->name, PRM_NAME_INTL_NUMBER_LANG) == 0 || strcmp (prm->name, PRM_NAME_INTL_DATE_LANG) == 0)
8623  {
8624  INTL_LANG dummy;
8625 
8626  if (lang_get_lang_id_from_name (value, &dummy) != 0)
8627  {
8628  return PRM_ERR_BAD_VALUE;
8629  }
8630  }
8631  if (strcmp (prm->name, PRM_NAME_INTL_COLLATION) == 0)
8632  {
8633  LANG_COLLATION *lc = NULL;
8634  if (value != NULL)
8635  {
8636  lc = lang_get_collation_by_name (value);
8637  }
8638 
8639  if (lc == NULL)
8640  {
8641  return PRM_ERR_BAD_VALUE;
8642  }
8643  }
8644  if (strcmp (prm->name, PRM_NAME_TIMEZONE) == 0)
8645  {
8646  int er_status = NO_ERROR;
8647 
8648  if (value != NULL)
8649  {
8650  er_status = tz_str_to_region (value, strlen (value), NULL);
8651  if (er_status != NO_ERROR)
8652  {
8653  return PRM_ERR_BAD_VALUE;
8654  }
8655  }
8656  }
8657  }
8658 #endif
8659  if (set_max || set_min)
8660  {
8661  ret = sysprm_get_param_range (prm, &min, &max);
8662  if (ret != PRM_ERR_NO_ERROR)
8663  {
8664  return PRM_ERR_BAD_VALUE;
8665  }
8666  if (set_min)
8667  {
8668  *new_value = min;
8669  }
8670  else
8671  {
8672  *new_value = max;
8673  }
8674  return PRM_ERR_NO_ERROR;
8675  }
8676  switch (prm->datatype)
8677  {
8678  case PRM_INTEGER:
8679  {
8680  /* convert string to int */
8681  int val;
8682 
8683  if (set_default)
8684  {
8685  new_value->i = PRM_GET_INT (prm->default_value);
8686  break;
8687  }
8688 
8689  if (PRM_HAS_SIZE_UNIT (prm->static_flag))
8690  {
8691  UINT64 dup_val;
8692  if (util_size_string_to_byte (&dup_val, value) != NO_ERROR)
8693  {
8694  return PRM_ERR_BAD_VALUE;
8695  }
8696 
8697  if (prm_check_range (prm, (void *) &dup_val) != NO_ERROR)
8698  {
8699  return PRM_ERR_BAD_RANGE;
8700  }
8701 
8702  if (PRM_DIFFERENT_UNIT (prm->static_flag))
8703  {
8704  PRM_ADJUST_FOR_SET_BIGINT_TO_INTEGER (prm, &val, &dup_val, &error);
8705  if (error != NO_ERROR)
8706  {
8707  return PRM_ERR_BAD_VALUE;
8708  }
8709  }
8710  else
8711  {
8712  return PRM_ERR_BAD_VALUE;
8713  }
8714  }
8715  else if (PRM_HAS_TIME_UNIT (prm->static_flag))
8716  {
8717  INT64 dup_val;
8718 
8719  if (util_time_string_to_msec (&dup_val, (char *) value) != NO_ERROR)
8720  {
8721  return PRM_ERR_BAD_VALUE;
8722  }
8723 
8724  if (prm_check_range (prm, (void *) &dup_val) != NO_ERROR)
8725  {
8726  return PRM_ERR_BAD_RANGE;
8727  }
8728 
8729  if (PRM_DIFFERENT_UNIT (prm->static_flag) && dup_val >= 0)
8730  {
8731  UINT64 tmp_val = (UINT64) dup_val;
8732  PRM_ADJUST_FOR_SET_BIGINT_TO_INTEGER (prm, &val, &tmp_val, &error);
8733  if (error != NO_ERROR)
8734  {
8735  return PRM_ERR_BAD_VALUE;
8736  }
8737  }
8738  else
8739  {
8740  val = (int) dup_val;
8741  }
8742  }
8743  else
8744  {
8745  int result;
8746 
8747  result = parse_int (&val, value, 10);
8748 
8749  if (result != 0)
8750  {
8751  return PRM_ERR_BAD_VALUE;
8752  }
8753 
8754  if (prm_check_range (prm, (void *) &val) != NO_ERROR)
8755  {
8756  return PRM_ERR_BAD_RANGE;
8757  }
8758 
8759  if (PRM_DIFFERENT_UNIT (prm->static_flag))
8760  {
8761  PRM_ADJUST_FOR_SET_INTEGER_TO_INTEGER (prm, &val, &val, &error);
8762  if (error != NO_ERROR)
8763  {
8764  return PRM_ERR_BAD_VALUE;
8765  }
8766  }
8767  }
8768 
8769  new_value->i = val;
8770  break;
8771  }
8772 
8773  case PRM_BIGINT:
8774  {
8775  /* convert string to UINT64 */
8776  int result;
8777  UINT64 val;
8778  char *end_p;
8779 
8780  if (set_default)
8781  {
8782  new_value->bi = PRM_GET_BIGINT (prm->default_value);
8783  break;
8784  }
8785 
8786  if (PRM_HAS_SIZE_UNIT (prm->static_flag))
8787  {
8788  if (util_size_string_to_byte (&val, value) != NO_ERROR)
8789  {
8790  return PRM_ERR_BAD_VALUE;
8791  }
8792  }
8793  else
8794  {
8795  result = str_to_uint64 (&val, &end_p, value, 10);
8796  if (result != 0)
8797  {
8798  return PRM_ERR_BAD_VALUE;
8799  }
8800  }
8801 
8802  if (prm_check_range (prm, (void *) &val) != NO_ERROR)
8803  {
8804  return PRM_ERR_BAD_RANGE;
8805  }
8806 
8807  if (PRM_DIFFERENT_UNIT (prm->static_flag))
8808  {
8809  PRM_ADJUST_FOR_SET_BIGINT_TO_BIGINT (prm, &val, &val, &error);
8810  if (error != NO_ERROR)
8811  {
8812  return PRM_ERR_BAD_VALUE;
8813  }
8814  }
8815 
8816  new_value->bi = val;
8817  break;
8818  }
8819 
8820  case PRM_FLOAT:
8821  {
8822  /* convert string to float */
8823  float val;
8824 
8825  if (set_default)
8826  {
8827  new_value->f = PRM_GET_FLOAT (prm->default_value);
8828  break;
8829  }
8830 
8831  if (PRM_HAS_SIZE_UNIT (prm->static_flag))
8832  {
8833  UINT64 dup_val;
8834  if (util_size_string_to_byte (&dup_val, value) != NO_ERROR)
8835  {
8836  return PRM_ERR_BAD_VALUE;
8837  }
8838 
8839  if (prm_check_range (prm, (void *) &dup_val) != NO_ERROR)
8840  {
8841  return PRM_ERR_BAD_RANGE;
8842  }
8843 
8844  if (PRM_DIFFERENT_UNIT (prm->static_flag))
8845  {
8846  PRM_ADJUST_FOR_SET_BIGINT_TO_FLOAT (prm, &val, &dup_val, &error);
8847  if (error != NO_ERROR)
8848  {
8849  return PRM_ERR_BAD_VALUE;
8850  }
8851  }
8852  else
8853  {
8854  return PRM_ERR_BAD_VALUE;
8855  }
8856  }
8857  else
8858  {
8859  val = (float) strtod (value, &end);
8860  if (end == value)
8861  {
8862  return PRM_ERR_BAD_VALUE;
8863  }
8864  else if (*end != '\0')
8865  {
8866  return PRM_ERR_BAD_VALUE;
8867  }
8868 
8869  if (prm_check_range (prm, (void *) &val) != NO_ERROR)
8870  {
8871  return PRM_ERR_BAD_RANGE;
8872  }
8873 
8874  if (PRM_DIFFERENT_UNIT (prm->static_flag))
8875  {
8876  PRM_ADJUST_FOR_SET_FLOAT_TO_FLOAT (prm, &val, &val, &error);
8877  if (error != NO_ERROR)
8878  {
8879  return PRM_ERR_BAD_VALUE;
8880  }
8881  }
8882  }
8883 
8884  new_value->f = val;
8885  break;
8886  }
8887 
8888  case PRM_BOOLEAN:
8889  {
8890  const KEYVAL *keyvalp = NULL;
8891 
8892  if (set_default)
8893  {
8894  new_value->b = PRM_GET_BOOL (prm->default_value);
8895  break;
8896  }
8897 
8898  /* convert string to boolean */
8899 
8900  keyvalp = prm_keyword (-1, value, boolean_words, DIM (boolean_words));
8901  if (keyvalp == NULL)
8902  {
8903  return PRM_ERR_BAD_VALUE;
8904  }
8905 
8906  new_value->b = (bool) keyvalp->val;
8907  break;
8908  }
8909 
8910  case PRM_STRING:
8911  {
8912  /* duplicate string */
8913  const char *val = NULL;
8914 
8915  if (set_default)
8916  {
8917  val = PRM_GET_STRING (prm->default_value);
8918  if (val == NULL)
8919  {
8920  switch (sysprm_get_id (prm))
8921  {
8922  case PRM_ID_INTL_COLLATION:
8923  val = lang_get_collation_name (LANG_GET_BINARY_COLLATION (LANG_SYS_CODESET));
8924  break;
8925  case PRM_ID_INTL_DATE_LANG:
8926  case PRM_ID_INTL_NUMBER_LANG:
8927  val = lang_get_Lang_name ();
8928  break;
8929  case PRM_ID_TIMEZONE:
8930  val = prm_get_string_value (PRM_ID_SERVER_TIMEZONE);
8931  break;
8932  default:
8933  /* do nothing */
8934  break;
8935  }
8936  }
8937 
8938  if (val == NULL)
8939  {
8940  new_value->str = NULL;
8941  }
8942  else
8943  {
8944  new_value->str = strdup (val);
8945  if (new_value->str == NULL)
8946  {
8947  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, (size_t) (strlen (val)));
8948  return PRM_ERR_NO_MEM_FOR_PRM;
8949  }
8950  }
8951  break;
8952  }
8953 
8954  /* check if the value is represented as a null keyword */
8955  if (prm_keyword (-1, value, null_words, DIM (null_words)) != NULL)
8956  {
8957  new_value->str = NULL;
8958  }
8959  else
8960  {
8961  new_value->str = strdup (value);
8962  if (new_value->str == NULL)
8963  {
8964  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, (size_t) (strlen (value)));
8965  return PRM_ERR_NO_MEM_FOR_PRM;
8966  }
8967  }
8968  break;
8969  }
8970 
8971  case PRM_INTEGER_LIST:
8972  {
8973  /* convert string into an array of integers */
8974  int *val = NULL;
8975 
8976  if (set_default && sysprm_get_id (prm) != PRM_ID_CALL_STACK_DUMP_ACTIVATION)
8977  {
8978  val = PRM_GET_INTEGER_LIST (prm->default_value);
8979  if (val == NULL)
8980  {
8981  new_value->integer_list = NULL;
8982  }
8983  else
8984  {
8985  size_t size = (size_t) ((val[0] + 1) * sizeof (int));
8986  new_value->integer_list = (int *) malloc (size);
8987 
8988  if (new_value->integer_list == NULL)
8989  {
8990  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, size);
8991  return PRM_ERR_NO_MEM_FOR_PRM;
8992  }
8993 
8994  memcpy (new_value->integer_list, val, size);
8995  }
8996 
8997  break;
8998  }
8999 
9000  /* check if the value is represented as a null keyword */
9001  if (prm_keyword (-1, value, null_words, DIM (null_words)) != NULL)
9002  {
9003  val = NULL;
9004  }
9005  else
9006  {
9007  char *s, *p;
9008  char save;
9009  int list_size, tmp;
9010 
9011  val = (int *) calloc (1024, sizeof (int)); /* max size is 1023 */
9012  if (val == NULL)
9013  {
9014  size_t size = 1024 * sizeof (int);
9015  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, size);
9016  return PRM_ERR_NO_MEM_FOR_PRM;
9017  }
9018 
9019  list_size = 0;
9020  s = (char *) value;
9021  p = s;
9022 
9023  while (true)
9024  {
9025  if (*s == ',' || *s == '\0')
9026  {
9027  save = *s;
9028  *s = '\0';
9029  if (intl_mbs_casecmp ("default", p) == 0)
9030  {
9031  if (sysprm_get_id (prm) == PRM_ID_CALL_STACK_DUMP_ACTIVATION)
9032  {
9033  memcpy (&val[list_size + 1], call_stack_dump_error_codes,
9034  sizeof (call_stack_dump_error_codes));
9035  list_size += DIM (call_stack_dump_error_codes);
9036  }
9037  else
9038  {
9039  free_and_init (val);
9040  return PRM_ERR_BAD_VALUE;
9041  }
9042  }
9043  else
9044  {
9045  int result;
9046 
9047  result = parse_int (&tmp, p, 10);
9048  if (result != 0)
9049  {
9050  free_and_init (val);
9051  return PRM_ERR_BAD_VALUE;
9052  }
9053  val[++list_size] = tmp;
9054  }
9055  *s = save;
9056  if (*s == '\0')
9057  {
9058  break;
9059  }
9060  p = s + 1;
9061  }
9062  s++;
9063  }
9064  /* save size in the first position */
9065  val[0] = list_size;
9066  }
9067  new_value->integer_list = val;
9068  break;
9069  }
9070 
9071  case PRM_KEYWORD:
9072  {
9073  /* check if string can be identified as a keyword */
9074  int val;
9075  const KEYVAL *keyvalp = NULL;
9076 
9077  if (set_default)
9078  {
9079  new_value->i = PRM_GET_INT (prm->default_value);
9080  break;
9081  }
9082 
9083  if (intl_mbs_casecmp (prm->name, PRM_NAME_ER_LOG_LEVEL) == 0)
9084  {
9085  keyvalp = prm_keyword (-1, value, er_log_level_words, DIM (er_log_level_words));
9086  }
9087  else if (intl_mbs_casecmp (prm->name, PRM_NAME_LOG_ISOLATION_LEVEL) == 0)
9088  {
9089  keyvalp = prm_keyword (-1, value, isolation_level_words, DIM (isolation_level_words));
9090  }
9091  else if (intl_mbs_casecmp (prm->name, PRM_NAME_PB_DEBUG_PAGE_VALIDATION_LEVEL) == 0)
9092  {
9093  keyvalp =
9094  prm_keyword (-1, value, pgbuf_debug_page_validation_level_words,
9095  DIM (pgbuf_debug_page_validation_level_words));
9096  }
9097  else if (intl_mbs_casecmp (prm->name, PRM_NAME_HA_MODE) == 0
9098  || intl_mbs_casecmp (prm->name, PRM_NAME_HA_MODE_FOR_SA_UTILS_ONLY) == 0)
9099  {
9100  keyvalp = prm_keyword (-1, value, ha_mode_words, DIM (ha_mode_words));
9101  }
9102  else if (intl_mbs_casecmp (prm->name, PRM_NAME_HA_SERVER_STATE) == 0)
9103  {
9104  keyvalp = prm_keyword (-1, value, ha_server_state_words, DIM (ha_server_state_words));
9105  }
9106  else if (intl_mbs_casecmp (prm->name, PRM_NAME_HA_LOG_APPLIER_STATE) == 0)
9107  {
9108  keyvalp = prm_keyword (-1, value, ha_log_applier_state_words, DIM (ha_log_applier_state_words));
9109  }
9110  else if (intl_mbs_casecmp (prm->name, PRM_NAME_COMPAT_MODE) == 0)
9111  {
9112  keyvalp = prm_keyword (-1, value, compat_words, DIM (compat_words));
9113  }
9114  else if (intl_mbs_casecmp (prm->name, PRM_NAME_CHECK_PEER_ALIVE) == 0)
9115  {
9116  keyvalp = prm_keyword (-1, value, check_peer_alive_words, DIM (check_peer_alive_words));
9117  }
9118  else if (intl_mbs_casecmp (prm->name, PRM_NAME_QUERY_TRACE_FORMAT) == 0)
9119  {
9120  keyvalp = prm_keyword (-1, value, query_trace_format_words, DIM (query_trace_format_words));
9121  }
9122  else if (intl_mbs_casecmp (prm->name, PRM_NAME_FAULT_INJECTION_TEST) == 0)
9123  {
9124  keyvalp = prm_keyword (-1, value, fi_test_words, DIM (fi_test_words));
9125  }
9126  else if (intl_mbs_casecmp (prm->name, PRM_NAME_HA_REPL_FILTER_TYPE) == 0)
9127  {
9128  keyvalp = prm_keyword (-1, value, ha_repl_filter_type_words, DIM (ha_repl_filter_type_words));
9129  }
9130  else
9131  {
9132  assert (false);
9133  }
9134 
9135  if (keyvalp)
9136  {
9137  val = (int) keyvalp->val;
9138  }
9139  else
9140  {
9141  int result;
9142  /* check if string can be converted to an integer */
9143  result = parse_int (&val, value, 10);
9144  if (result != 0)
9145  {
9146  return PRM_ERR_BAD_VALUE;
9147  }
9148  }
9149 
9150  if ((prm->upper_limit && PRM_GET_INT (prm->upper_limit) < val)
9151  || (prm->lower_limit && PRM_GET_INT (prm->lower_limit) > val))
9152  {
9153  return PRM_ERR_BAD_RANGE;
9154  }
9155  new_value->i = val;
9156  }
9157  break;
9158  case PRM_NO_TYPE:
9159  break;
9160 
9161  default:
9162  assert (false);
9163  }
9164 
9165  return ret;
9166 }
9167 
9168 /*
9169  * prm_set () - Set a new value for parameter.
9170  *
9171  * return : SYSPRM_ERR code.
9172  * prm (in) : system parameter that will have its value changed.
9173  * value (in) : new value as string.
9174  * set_flag (in) : updates PRM_SET flag is true.
9175  */
9176 static int
9177 prm_set (SYSPRM_PARAM * prm, const char *value, bool set_flag)
9178 {
9179  SYSPRM_ERR error = PRM_ERR_NO_ERROR;
9180  SYSPRM_VALUE new_value;
9181 
9182  error = sysprm_generate_new_value (prm, value, false, &new_value);
9183  if (error != PRM_ERR_NO_ERROR)
9184  {
9185  return error;
9186  }
9187 
9188  return sysprm_set_value (prm, new_value, set_flag, false);
9189 }
9190 
9191 /*
9192  * sysprm_set_value () - Set a new value for parameter.
9193  *
9194  * return : SYSPRM_ERR code
9195  * prm (in) : system parameter that will have its value changed.
9196  * value (in) : new values as sysprm_value
9197  * set_flag (in) : updates PRM_SET flag.
9198  * duplicate (in) : duplicate values for data types that need memory
9199  * allocation.
9200  */
9201 static int
9202 sysprm_set_value (SYSPRM_PARAM * prm, SYSPRM_VALUE value, bool set_flag, bool duplicate)
9203 {
9204 #if defined (SERVER_MODE)
9205  PARAM_ID id;
9206  THREAD_ENTRY *thread_p;
9207 #endif
9208  void *tmp_ptr = NULL;
9209 
9210  if (prm == NULL)
9211  {
9212  return PRM_ERR_UNKNOWN_PARAM;
9213  }
9214 
9215  if (duplicate)
9216  {
9217  /* duplicate values for data types that need memory allocation */
9218  switch (prm->datatype)
9219  {
9220  case PRM_STRING:
9221  if (value.str != NULL)
9222  {
9223  tmp_ptr = strdup (value.str);
9224  if (tmp_ptr == NULL)
9225  {
9226  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1,
9227  (size_t) (strlen (value.str) + 1));
9228  return PRM_ERR_NO_MEM_FOR_PRM;
9229  }
9230 
9231  value.str = (char *) tmp_ptr;
9232  }
9233  break;
9234 
9235  case PRM_INTEGER_LIST:
9236  if (value.integer_list != NULL)
9237  {
9238  int *integer_list = value.integer_list;
9239  tmp_ptr = (int *) malloc ((integer_list[0] + 1) * sizeof (int));
9240  if (tmp_ptr == NULL)
9241  {
9242  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1,
9243  (integer_list[0] + 1) * sizeof (int));
9244  return PRM_ERR_NO_MEM_FOR_PRM;
9245  }
9246 
9247  value.integer_list = (int *) tmp_ptr;
9248  memcpy (value.integer_list, integer_list, (integer_list[0] + 1) * sizeof (int));
9249  }
9250 
9251  default:
9252  break;
9253  }
9254  }
9255 
9256 #if defined (SERVER_MODE)
9257  if (PRM_IS_FOR_SESSION (prm->static_flag) && BO_IS_SERVER_RESTARTED ())
9258  {
9259  SESSION_PARAM *param;
9260  TZ_REGION *session_tz_region;
9261 
9262  /* update session parameter */
9263  id = sysprm_get_id (prm);
9264  thread_p = thread_get_thread_entry_info ();
9265 
9266  param = session_get_session_parameter (thread_p, id);
9267  if (param == NULL)
9268  {
9269  if (tmp_ptr != NULL)
9270  {
9271  free (tmp_ptr);
9272  }
9273 
9274  return PRM_ERR_UNKNOWN_PARAM;
9275  }
9276 
9277  if (id == PRM_ID_TIMEZONE)
9278  {
9279  session_tz_region = session_get_session_tz_region (thread_p);
9280  if (session_tz_region != NULL)
9281  {
9282  tz_str_to_region (value.str, strlen (value.str), session_tz_region);
9283  }
9284  }
9285 
9286  return sysprm_set_session_parameter_value (param, id, value);
9287  }
9288 
9289  /* if prm is not for session or if session_parameters have not been initialized just set the system parameter stored
9290  * on server */
9291 #endif /* SERVER_MODE */
9292 
9293  sysprm_set_system_parameter_value (prm, value);
9294 
9295  /* Set the cached parsed system timezone region on the server */
9296  if (sysprm_get_id (prm) == PRM_ID_SERVER_TIMEZONE)
9297  {
9298  TZ_REGION tz_region_system;
9299  int err_status = 0;
9300 
9301  err_status = tz_str_to_region (value.str, strlen (value.str), &tz_region_system);
9302  if (err_status != NO_ERROR)
9303  {
9304  return PRM_ERR_BAD_PARAM;
9305  }
9306  tz_set_tz_region_system (&tz_region_system);
9307  }
9308 
9309  /* Set the cached parsed session timezone region on the client */
9310 #if !defined(SERVER_MODE)
9311  if (sysprm_get_id (prm) == PRM_ID_TIMEZONE)
9312  {
9313  int err_status = 0;
9314  err_status = tz_str_to_region (value.str, strlen (value.str), tz_get_client_tz_region_session ());
9315  if (err_status != NO_ERROR)
9316  {
9317  return PRM_ERR_BAD_PARAM;
9318  }
9319  }
9320 #endif
9321 
9322  if (PRM_IS_COMPOUND (prm->static_flag))
9323  {
9324  prm_compound_has_changed (prm, set_flag);
9325  }
9326 
9327  if (set_flag)
9328  {
9329  PRM_SET_BIT (PRM_SET, *prm->dynamic_flag);
9330  /* Indicate that the default value was not used */
9331  PRM_CLEAR_BIT (PRM_DEFAULT_USED, *prm->dynamic_flag);
9332  }
9333 
9334  return PRM_ERR_NO_ERROR;
9335 }
9336 
9337 /*
9338  * sysprm_set_system_parameter_value () - change a parameter value in prm_Def
9339  * array.
9340  *
9341  * return : void.
9342  * prm (in) : parameter that needs changed.
9343  * value (in) : new value.
9344  */
9345 static void
9346 sysprm_set_system_parameter_value (SYSPRM_PARAM * prm, SYSPRM_VALUE value)
9347 {
9348  PARAM_ID prm_id = sysprm_get_id (prm);
9349  switch (prm->datatype)
9350  {
9351  case PRM_INTEGER:
9352  case PRM_KEYWORD:
9353  prm_set_integer_value (prm_id, value.i);
9354  break;
9355 
9356  case PRM_FLOAT:
9357  prm_set_float_value (prm_id, value.f);
9358  break;
9359 
9360  case PRM_BOOLEAN:
9361  prm_set_bool_value (prm_id, value.b);
9362  break;
9363 
9364  case PRM_STRING:
9365  prm_set_string_value (prm_id, value.str);
9366  break;
9367 
9368  case PRM_INTEGER_LIST:
9369  prm_set_integer_list_value (prm_id, value.integer_list);
9370  break;
9371 
9372  case PRM_BIGINT:
9373  prm_set_bigint_value (prm_id, value.bi);
9374  break;
9375 
9376  default:
9377  assert_release (0);
9378  break;
9379  }
9380 }
9381 
9382 /*
9383  * prm_compound_has_changed () - update all affected system parameters if prm
9384  * is a compound.
9385  *
9386  * return : error code
9387  * prm (in) : system parameter that has changed
9388  * set_flag (in) : updates PRM_SET flag.
9389  */
9390 static int
9391 prm_compound_has_changed (SYSPRM_PARAM * prm, bool set_flag)
9392 {
9393  assert (PRM_IS_COMPOUND (prm->static_flag));
9394 
9395  if (sysprm_get_id (prm) == PRM_ID_COMPAT_MODE)
9396  {
9397  prm_set_compound (prm, compat_mode_values, DIM (compat_mode_values), set_flag);
9398  }
9399  else
9400  {
9401  assert (false);
9402  }
9403  return NO_ERROR;
9404 }
9405 
9406 
9407 /*
9408  * prm_set_force -
9409  * return: NO_ERROR or error code defined in enum SYSPRM_ERR
9410  * prm(in):
9411  * value(in):
9412  */
9413 static int
9414 prm_set_force (SYSPRM_PARAM * prm, const char *value)
9415 {
9416  if (prm->force_value)
9417  {
9418  free_and_init (PRM_GET_STRING (&prm->force_value));
9419  }
9420 
9421  prm->force_value = strdup (value);
9422  if (prm->force_value == NULL)
9423  {
9424  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, (size_t) (strlen (value) + 1));
9425  return PRM_ERR_NO_MEM_FOR_PRM;
9426  }
9427 
9428  return NO_ERROR;
9429 }
9430 
9431 /*
9432  * prm_set_default -
9433  * return: NO_ERROR or error code defined in enum SYSPRM_ERR
9434  * prm(in):
9435  */
9436 static int
9437 prm_set_default (SYSPRM_PARAM * prm)
9438 {
9439 #if defined (SERVER_MODE)
9440  if (PRM_IS_FOR_SESSION (prm->static_flag) && BO_IS_SERVER_RESTARTED ())
9441  {
9442  PARAM_ID id;
9443  SESSION_PARAM *sprm = NULL;
9444  THREAD_ENTRY *thread_p = thread_get_thread_entry_info ();
9445 
9446  id = sysprm_get_id (prm);
9447  sprm = session_get_session_parameter (thread_p, id);
9448  if (sprm == NULL)
9449  {
9450  return PRM_ERR_UNKNOWN_PARAM;
9451  }
9452 
9453  return sysprm_set_session_parameter_default (sprm, id);
9454  }
9455 #endif /* SERVER_MODE */
9456 
9457  if (prm == NULL)
9458  {
9459  return ER_FAILED;
9460  }
9461 
9462  if (PRM_IS_INTEGER (prm) || PRM_IS_KEYWORD (prm))
9463  {
9464  int val, *valp;
9465 
9466  val = PRM_GET_INT (prm->default_value);
9467  valp = (int *) prm->value;
9468  *valp = val;
9469  }
9470  if (PRM_IS_BIGINT (prm))
9471  {
9472  UINT64 val, *valp;
9473 
9474  val = PRM_GET_BIGINT (prm->default_value);
9475  valp = (UINT64 *) prm->value;
9476  *valp = val;
9477  }
9478  else if (PRM_IS_BOOLEAN (prm))
9479  {
9480  bool val, *valp;
9481 
9482  val = PRM_GET_BOOL (prm->default_value);
9483  valp = (bool *) prm->value;
9484  *valp = val;
9485  }
9486  else if (PRM_IS_FLOAT (prm))
9487  {
9488  float val, *valp;
9489 
9490  val = PRM_GET_FLOAT (prm->default_value);
9491  valp = (float *) prm->value;
9492  *valp = val;
9493  }
9494  else if (PRM_IS_STRING (prm))
9495  {
9496  char *val, **valp;
9497 
9498  if (PRM_IS_ALLOCATED (*prm->dynamic_flag))
9499  {
9500  char *str = PRM_GET_STRING (prm->value);
9501  free_and_init (str);
9502  PRM_CLEAR_BIT (PRM_ALLOCATED, *prm->dynamic_flag);
9503  }
9504 
9505  val = *(char **) prm->default_value;
9506  valp = (char **) prm->value;
9507  *valp = val;
9508  }
9509  else if (PRM_IS_INTEGER_LIST (prm))
9510  {
9511  int *val, **valp;
9512 
9513  if (PRM_IS_ALLOCATED (*prm->dynamic_flag))
9514  {
9515  int *int_list = PRM_GET_INTEGER_LIST (prm->value);
9516 
9517  free_and_init (int_list);
9518  PRM_CLEAR_BIT (PRM_ALLOCATED, *prm->dynamic_flag);
9519  }
9520 
9521  val = *(int **) prm->default_value;
9522  valp = (int **) prm->value;
9523  *valp = val;
9524  }
9525 
9526  /* Indicate that the default value was used */
9527  PRM_SET_BIT (PRM_DEFAULT_USED, *prm->dynamic_flag);
9528 
9529  if (PRM_IS_FOR_QRY_STRING (prm->static_flag))
9530  {
9531  PRM_CLEAR_BIT (PRM_DIFFERENT, *prm->dynamic_flag);
9532  }
9533 
9534  return NO_ERROR;
9535 }
9536 
9537 /*
9538  * prm_find -
9539  * return: NULL or found parameter
9540  * pname(in): parameter name to find
9541  */
9542 static SYSPRM_PARAM *
9543 prm_find (const char *pname, const char *section)
9544 {
9545  unsigned int i;
9546  char *key;
9547  char buf[4096];
9548 
9549  if (pname == NULL)
9550  {
9551  return NULL;
9552  }
9553 
9554  if (section != NULL)
9555  {
9556  snprintf (buf, sizeof (buf) - 1, "%s::%s", section, pname);
9557  key = buf;
9558  }
9559  else
9560  {
9561  key = (char *) pname;
9562  }
9563 
9564  for (i = 0; i < DIM (prm_Def); i++)
9565  {
9566  if (intl_mbs_casecmp (prm_Def[i].name, key) == 0)
9567  {
9568  return &prm_Def[i];
9569  }
9570  }
9571 
9572  return NULL;
9573 }
9574 
9575 /*
9576  * sysprm_set_force -
9577  * return: NO_ERROR or error code
9578  * pname(in): parameter name to set
9579  * pvalue(in): value to be set to the parameter
9580  */
9581 int
9582 sysprm_set_force (const char *pname, const char *pvalue)
9583 {
9584  SYSPRM_PARAM *prm;
9585 
9586  if (pname == NULL || pvalue == NULL)
9587  {
9588  return ER_PRM_BAD_VALUE;
9589  }
9590 
9591  prm = prm_find (pname, NULL);
9592  if (prm == NULL)
9593  {
9594  return ER_PRM_BAD_VALUE;
9595  }
9596 
9597  if (prm_set_force (prm, pvalue) != NO_ERROR)
9598  {
9599  return ER_PRM_CANNOT_CHANGE;
9600  }
9601 
9602  return NO_ERROR;
9603 }
9604 
9605 /*
9606  * sysprm_set_to_default -
9607  * return: NO_ERROR or error code
9608  * pname(in): parameter name to set to default value
9609  */
9610 int
9611 sysprm_set_to_default (const char *pname, bool set_to_force)
9612 {
9613  SYSPRM_PARAM *prm;
9614  char val[LINE_MAX];
9615 
9616  if (pname == NULL)
9617  {
9618  return ER_PRM_BAD_VALUE;
9619  }
9620 
9621  prm = prm_find (pname, NULL);
9622  if (prm == NULL)
9623  {
9624  return ER_PRM_BAD_VALUE;
9625  }
9626 
9627  if (prm_set_default (prm) != NO_ERROR)
9628  {
9629  return ER_PRM_CANNOT_CHANGE;
9630  }
9631 
9632  if (set_to_force)
9633  {
9634  prm_print (prm, val, LINE_MAX, PRM_PRINT_NONE, PRM_PRINT_CURR_VAL);
9635  prm_set_force (prm, val);
9636  }
9637 
9638  return NO_ERROR;
9639 }
9640 
9641 /*
9642  * prm_keyword - Search a keyword within the keyword table
9643  * return: NULL or found keyword
9644  * val(in): keyword value
9645  * name(in): keyword name
9646  * tbl(in): keyword table
9647  * dim(in): size of the table
9648  */
9649 static const KEYVAL *
9650 prm_keyword (int val, const char *name, const KEYVAL * tbl, int dim)
9651 {
9652  int i;
9653 
9654  if (name != NULL)
9655  {
9656  for (i = 0; i < dim; i++)
9657  {
9658  if (intl_mbs_casecmp (name, tbl[i].key) == 0)
9659  {
9660  return &tbl[i];
9661  }
9662  }
9663  }
9664  else
9665  {
9666  for (i = 0; i < dim; i++)
9667  {
9668  if (tbl[i].val == val)
9669  {
9670  return &tbl[i];
9671  }
9672  }
9673  }
9674 
9675  return NULL;
9676 }
9677 
9678 /*
9679  * prm_report_bad_entry -
9680  * return:
9681  * line(in):
9682  * err(in):
9683  * where(in):
9684  */
9685 static void
9686 prm_report_bad_entry (const char *key, int line, int err, const char *where)
9687 {
9688  if (line > 0)
9689  {
9690  fprintf (stderr, PARAM_MSG_FMT (PRM_ERR_BAD_LINE), key, line, where);
9691  }
9692  else if (line == 0)
9693  {
9694  fprintf (stderr, PARAM_MSG_FMT (PRM_ERR_BAD_PARAM), key, line, where);
9695  }
9696  else
9697  {
9698  fprintf (stderr, PARAM_MSG_FMT (PRM_ERR_BAD_ENV_VAR), where);
9699  }
9700 
9701  if (err > 0)
9702  {
9703  switch (err)
9704  {
9705  case PRM_ERR_DEPRICATED:
9706  case PRM_ERR_NO_MEM_FOR_PRM:
9707  fprintf (stderr, "%s\n", PARAM_MSG_FMT (err));
9708  break;
9709 
9710  case PRM_ERR_UNKNOWN_PARAM:
9711  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_PRM_UNKNOWN_SYSPRM, 3, key, line, where);
9712  fprintf (stderr, "%s\n", PARAM_MSG_FMT (err));
9713  break;
9714 
9715  case PRM_ERR_BAD_VALUE:
9716  case PRM_ERR_BAD_STRING:
9717  case PRM_ERR_BAD_RANGE:
9718  case PRM_ERR_RESET_BAD_RANGE:
9719  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_PRM_BAD_VALUE, 1, key);
9720  fprintf (stderr, "%s\n", PARAM_MSG_FMT (err));
9721  break;
9722 
9723  default:
9724  break;
9725  }
9726  }
9727  else
9728  {
9729  fprintf (stderr, PARAM_MSG_FMT (PRM_ERR_UNIX_ERROR), strerror (err));
9730  }
9731 
9732  fflush (stderr);
9733 }
9734 
9735 
9736 /*
9737  * sysprm_final - Clean up the storage allocated during parameter parsing
9738  * return: none
9739  */
9740 void
9741 sysprm_final (void)
9742 {
9743  SYSPRM_PARAM *prm;
9744  int i;
9745 
9746  for (i = 0; i < NUM_PRM; i++)
9747  {
9748  prm = &prm_Def[i];
9749  if (PRM_IS_ALLOCATED (*prm->dynamic_flag))
9750  {
9751  switch (prm->datatype)
9752  {
9753  case PRM_STRING:
9754  free_and_init (PRM_GET_STRING (prm->value));
9755  PRM_CLEAR_BIT (PRM_ALLOCATED, *prm->dynamic_flag);
9756  break;
9757 
9758  case PRM_INTEGER_LIST:
9759  free_and_init (PRM_GET_INTEGER_LIST (prm->value));
9760  PRM_CLEAR_BIT (PRM_ALLOCATED, *prm->dynamic_flag);
9761  break;
9762 
9763  default:
9764  /* do nothing */
9765  break;
9766  }
9767  }
9768 
9769  /* reset all dynamic flags */
9770  *prm->dynamic_flag = 0;
9771  }
9772 
9773  for (i = 0; i < MAX_NUM_OF_PRM_FILES_LOADED; i++)
9774  {
9775  if (prm_Files_loaded[i].conf_path != NULL)
9776  {
9777  free_and_init (prm_Files_loaded[i].conf_path);
9778  }
9779  if (prm_Files_loaded[i].db_name != NULL)
9780  {
9781  free_and_init (prm_Files_loaded[i].db_name);
9782  }
9783  }
9784 }
9785 
9786 #if defined (SA_MODE) || defined (SERVER_MODE)
9787 static void
9788 init_server_timezone_parameter (void)
9789 {
9790  SYSPRM_PARAM *prm_server_timezone;
9791 
9792  prm_server_timezone = prm_find (PRM_NAME_SERVER_TIMEZONE, NULL);
9793 
9794  if (prm_server_timezone != NULL && !PRM_IS_SET (*prm_server_timezone->dynamic_flag))
9795  {
9796  char timezone_name[TZ_GENERIC_NAME_SIZE + 1];
9797  int ret;
9798 
9799  if (PRM_GET_STRING (prm_server_timezone->value))
9800  {
9801  free_and_init (PRM_GET_STRING (prm_server_timezone->value));
9802  }
9803  PRM_CLEAR_BIT (PRM_ALLOCATED, *prm_server_timezone->dynamic_flag);
9804 
9805  ret = tz_resolve_os_timezone (timezone_name, TZ_GENERIC_NAME_SIZE);
9806  if (ret < 0)
9807  {
9808  if (tz_get_data () != NULL)
9809  {
9810  strcpy (timezone_name, "Asia/Seoul");
9811  }
9812  else
9813  {
9814  /* IANA timezone data not available, just use offset timezone */
9815  strcpy (timezone_name, "+09:00");
9816  }
9817  }
9818  prm_set (prm_server_timezone, timezone_name, true);
9819  }
9820 }

9823 /*
9824  * prm_tune_parameters - Sets the values of various system parameters
9825  * depending on the value of other parameters
9826  * return: none
9827  *
9828  * Note: Used for providing a mechanism for tuning various system parameters.
9829  * The parameters are only tuned if the user has not set them
9830  * explictly, this can be ascertained by checking if the default
9831  * value has been used.
9832  */
9833 #if defined (SA_MODE) || defined (SERVER_MODE)
9834 static void
9835 prm_tune_parameters (void)
9836 {
9837  SYSPRM_PARAM *pb_aout_ratio_prm;
9838  SYSPRM_PARAM *max_clients_prm;
9839  SYSPRM_PARAM *max_plan_cache_entries_prm;
9840  SYSPRM_PARAM *query_cache_mode_prm;
9841  SYSPRM_PARAM *max_query_cache_entries_prm;
9842  SYSPRM_PARAM *query_cache_size_in_pages_prm;
9843  SYSPRM_PARAM *ha_mode_prm;
9844  SYSPRM_PARAM *ha_server_state_prm;
9845  SYSPRM_PARAM *auto_restart_server_prm;
9846  SYSPRM_PARAM *log_background_archiving_prm;
9847  SYSPRM_PARAM *ha_node_list_prm;
9848  SYSPRM_PARAM *max_log_archives_prm;
9849  SYSPRM_PARAM *force_remove_log_archives_prm;
9850  SYSPRM_PARAM *call_stack_dump_activation_prm;
9851  SYSPRM_PARAM *fault_injection_ids_prm;
9852  SYSPRM_PARAM *fault_injection_test_prm;
9853  SYSPRM_PARAM *test_mode_prm;
9854  SYSPRM_PARAM *tz_leap_second_support_prm;
9855 
9856  char newval[LINE_MAX];
9857  char host_name[MAXHOSTNAMELEN];
9858  int max_clients;
9859 
9860  /* Find the parameters that require tuning */
9861  pb_aout_ratio_prm = prm_find (PRM_NAME_PB_AOUT_RATIO, NULL);
9862  max_clients_prm = prm_find (PRM_NAME_CSS_MAX_CLIENTS, NULL);
9863  max_plan_cache_entries_prm = prm_find (PRM_NAME_XASL_CACHE_MAX_ENTRIES, NULL);
9864  query_cache_mode_prm = prm_find (PRM_NAME_LIST_QUERY_CACHE_MODE, NULL);
9865  max_query_cache_entries_prm = prm_find (PRM_NAME_LIST_MAX_QUERY_CACHE_ENTRIES, NULL);
