9868  tz_leap_second_support_prm = prm_find (PRM_NAME_TZ_LEAP_SECOND_SUPPORT, NULL);
9869 
9870  /* disable AOUT list until we fix CBRD-20741 */
9871  if (pb_aout_ratio_prm != NULL)
9872  {
9873  prm_set (pb_aout_ratio_prm, "0", false);
9874  }
9875 
9876  /* temporarily modifies the query result cache feature to be disabled in RB-8.2.2. because it is not verified on 64
9877  * bit environment. */
9878  if (query_cache_mode_prm != NULL)
9879  {
9880  prm_set (query_cache_mode_prm, "0", false);
9881  }
9882 
9883  ha_mode_prm = prm_find (PRM_NAME_HA_MODE, NULL);
9884  ha_server_state_prm = prm_find (PRM_NAME_HA_SERVER_STATE, NULL);
9885  auto_restart_server_prm = prm_find (PRM_NAME_AUTO_RESTART_SERVER, NULL);
9886  log_background_archiving_prm = prm_find (PRM_NAME_LOG_BACKGROUND_ARCHIVING, NULL);
9887  ha_node_list_prm = prm_find (PRM_NAME_HA_NODE_LIST, NULL);
9888  max_log_archives_prm = prm_find (PRM_NAME_LOG_MAX_ARCHIVES, NULL);
9889  force_remove_log_archives_prm = prm_find (PRM_NAME_FORCE_REMOVE_LOG_ARCHIVES, NULL);
9890 
9891  /* Check that max clients has been set */
9892  assert (max_clients_prm != NULL);
9893  if (max_clients_prm == NULL)
9894  {
9895  return;
9896  }
9897 
9898 #if 0
9899  if (!(PRM_IS_SET (*max_clients_prm->dynamic_flag)))
9900  {
9901  if (prm_set_default (max_clients_prm) != PRM_ERR_NO_ERROR)
9902  {
9903  fprintf (stderr, msgcat_message (MSGCAT_CATALOG_CUBRID, MSGCAT_SET_PARAMETERS, PRM_ERR_NO_VALUE),
9904  max_clients_prm->name);
9905  assert (0);
9906  return;
9907  }
9908  }
9909  else
9910 #endif
9911  {
9912  max_clients = MIN (prm_css_max_clients_upper, css_get_max_socket_fds ());
9913  if (PRM_GET_INT (max_clients_prm->value) > max_clients)
9914  {
9915  sprintf (newval, "%d", max_clients);
9916  (void) prm_set (max_clients_prm, newval, false);
9917  }
9918  }
9919 
9920  /* check Plan Cache and Query Cache parameters */
9921  assert (max_plan_cache_entries_prm != NULL);
9922  assert (query_cache_mode_prm != NULL);
9923  assert (max_query_cache_entries_prm != NULL);
9924  assert (query_cache_size_in_pages_prm != NULL);
9925 
9926  if (max_plan_cache_entries_prm == NULL || query_cache_mode_prm == NULL || max_query_cache_entries_prm == NULL)
9927  {
9928  return;
9929  }
9930 
9931  if (PRM_GET_INT (max_plan_cache_entries_prm->value) == 0)
9932  {
9933  /* 0 means disable plan cache */
9934  (void) prm_set (max_plan_cache_entries_prm, "-1", false);
9935  }
9936 
9937  if (PRM_GET_INT (max_plan_cache_entries_prm->value) <= 0)
9938  {
9939  /* disable all by default */
9940  (void) prm_set_default (query_cache_mode_prm);
9941  (void) prm_set_default (max_query_cache_entries_prm);
9942  (void) prm_set_default (query_cache_size_in_pages_prm);
9943  }
9944  else
9945  {
9946  if (PRM_GET_INT (query_cache_mode_prm->value) == 0)
9947  {
9948  (void) prm_set_default (max_query_cache_entries_prm);
9949  (void) prm_set_default (query_cache_size_in_pages_prm);
9950  }
9951  else
9952  {
9953  if (PRM_GET_INT (max_query_cache_entries_prm->value) <= 0)
9954  {
9955  sprintf (newval, "%d", PRM_GET_INT (max_plan_cache_entries_prm->value));
9956  (void) prm_set (max_query_cache_entries_prm, newval, false);
9957  }
9958  }
9959  }
9960 
9961  /* check HA related parameters */
9962  assert (ha_mode_prm != NULL);
9963  assert (auto_restart_server_prm != NULL);
9964  if (ha_mode_prm == NULL || ha_server_state_prm == NULL || auto_restart_server_prm == NULL)
9965  {
9966  return;
9967  }
9968 
9969 #if defined (SA_MODE) || defined (WINDOWS)
9970  /* we should save original PRM_HA_MODE value before tuning */
9971  PRM_HA_MODE_FOR_SA_UTILS_ONLY = PRM_HA_MODE;
9972 
9973  /* reset to default 'active mode' */
9974  (void) prm_set_default (ha_mode_prm);
9975  (void) prm_set (ha_server_state_prm, HA_SERVER_STATE_ACTIVE_STR, false);
9976 
9977  if (force_remove_log_archives_prm != NULL && !PRM_GET_BOOL (force_remove_log_archives_prm->value))
9978  {
9979  (void) prm_set_default (max_log_archives_prm);
9980  }
9981 #else /* SA_MODE || WINDOWS */
9982  if (PRM_GET_INT (ha_mode_prm->value) != HA_MODE_OFF)
9983  {
9984  if (PRM_DEFAULT_VAL_USED (*ha_server_state_prm->dynamic_flag))
9985  {
9986  sprintf (newval, "%s", HA_SERVER_STATE_STANDBY_STR);
9987  prm_set (ha_server_state_prm, newval, false);
9988  }
9989  prm_set (auto_restart_server_prm, "no", false);
9990 
9991  if (PRM_GET_INT (ha_mode_prm->value) == HA_MODE_REPLICA)
9992  {
9993  prm_set (force_remove_log_archives_prm, "yes", false);
9994  }
9995  }
9996  else
9997  {
9998  sprintf (newval, "%s", HA_SERVER_STATE_ACTIVE_STR);
9999  prm_set (ha_server_state_prm, newval, false);
10000 
10001  if (force_remove_log_archives_prm != NULL && !PRM_GET_BOOL (force_remove_log_archives_prm->value))
10002  {
10003  (void) prm_set_default (max_log_archives_prm);
10004  }
10005  }
10006 #endif /* !SA_MODE && !WINDOWS */
10007  /* disable them temporarily */
10008 
10009  if (ha_node_list_prm == NULL || PRM_DEFAULT_VAL_USED (*ha_node_list_prm->dynamic_flag))
10010  {
10011  if (GETHOSTNAME (host_name, sizeof (host_name)))
10012  {
10013  strncpy (host_name, "localhost", sizeof (host_name) - 1);
10014  }
10015 
10016  snprintf (newval, sizeof (newval) - 1, "%s@%s", host_name, host_name);
10017  prm_set (ha_node_list_prm, newval, false);
10018  }
10019 
10020  call_stack_dump_activation_prm = GET_PRM (PRM_ID_CALL_STACK_DUMP_ACTIVATION);
10021  if (!PRM_IS_SET (*call_stack_dump_activation_prm->dynamic_flag))
10022  {
10023  int dim;
10024  int *integer_list = NULL;
10025 
10026  if (PRM_IS_ALLOCATED (*call_stack_dump_activation_prm->dynamic_flag))
10027  {
10028  free_and_init (PRM_GET_INTEGER_LIST (call_stack_dump_activation_prm->value));
10029  }
10030 
10031  dim = DIM (call_stack_dump_error_codes);
10032  integer_list = (int *) malloc ((dim + 1) * sizeof (int));
10033  if (integer_list == NULL)
10034  {
10035  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, (dim + 1) * sizeof (int));
10036  return;
10037  }
10038 
10039  integer_list[0] = dim;
10040  memcpy (&integer_list[1], call_stack_dump_error_codes, dim * sizeof (int));
10041  prm_set_integer_list_value (PRM_ID_CALL_STACK_DUMP_ACTIVATION, integer_list);
10042  PRM_SET_BIT (PRM_SET, *call_stack_dump_activation_prm->dynamic_flag);
10043  PRM_CLEAR_BIT (PRM_DEFAULT_USED, *call_stack_dump_activation_prm->dynamic_flag);
10044  }
10045 
10046 #if !defined(NDEBUG)
10047  fault_injection_ids_prm = GET_PRM (PRM_ID_FAULT_INJECTION_IDS);
10048  fault_injection_test_prm = GET_PRM (PRM_ID_FAULT_INJECTION_TEST);
10049  if (PRM_IS_SET (*fault_injection_test_prm->dynamic_flag))
10050  {
10051  int group_code;
10052  int dim;
10053  int *integer_list = NULL;
10054 
10055  group_code = PRM_GET_INT (fault_injection_test_prm->value);
10056 
10057  if (PRM_IS_ALLOCATED (*fault_injection_ids_prm->dynamic_flag))
10058  {
10059  free_and_init (PRM_GET_INTEGER_LIST (fault_injection_ids_prm->value));
10060  }
10061 
10062  for (dim = 0; fi_Groups[group_code][dim] != FI_TEST_NONE; dim++)
10063  {
10064  ;
10065  }
10066 
10067  integer_list = (int *) malloc ((dim + 1) * sizeof (int));
10068  if (integer_list == NULL)
10069  {
10070  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, (dim + 1) * sizeof (int));
10071  return;
10072  }
10073 
10074  integer_list[0] = dim;
10075  memcpy (&integer_list[1], fi_Groups[group_code], dim * sizeof (int));
10076  prm_set_integer_list_value (PRM_ID_FAULT_INJECTION_IDS, integer_list);
10077  PRM_SET_BIT (PRM_SET, *fault_injection_ids_prm->dynamic_flag);
10078  PRM_CLEAR_BIT (PRM_DEFAULT_USED, *fault_injection_ids_prm->dynamic_flag);
10079  }
10080 #endif
10081 
10082  if (PRM_GET_BOOL (test_mode_prm->value) == true)
10083  {
10084  tz_leap_second_support_prm->static_flag |= PRM_FOR_QRY_STRING;
10085  }
10086 
10087  return;
10088 }
10089 #else /* SA_MODE || SERVER_MODE */
10090 static void
10091 prm_tune_parameters (void)
10092 {
10093  SYSPRM_PARAM *max_plan_cache_entries_prm;
10094  SYSPRM_PARAM *ha_node_list_prm;

10103 
10104  char newval[LINE_MAX];
10105  char host_name[MAXHOSTNAMELEN];
10106 
10107  /* Find the parameters that require tuning */
10108  max_plan_cache_entries_prm = prm_find (PRM_NAME_XASL_CACHE_MAX_ENTRIES, NULL);
10109  ha_node_list_prm = prm_find (PRM_NAME_HA_NODE_LIST, NULL);

10112  ha_process_dereg_confirm_interval_in_msecs_prm = prm_find (PRM_NAME_HA_PROCESS_DEREG_CONFIRM_INTERVAL_IN_MSECS, NULL);

10116  ha_check_disk_failure_interval_prm = prm_find (PRM_NAME_HA_CHECK_DISK_FAILURE_INTERVAL_IN_SECS, NULL);
10117  test_mode_prm = prm_find (PRM_NAME_TEST_MODE, NULL);
10118  tz_leap_second_support_prm = prm_find (PRM_NAME_TZ_LEAP_SECOND_SUPPORT, NULL);
10119 
10120  assert (max_plan_cache_entries_prm != NULL);
10121  if (max_plan_cache_entries_prm == NULL)
10122  {
10123  return;
10124  }
10125 
10126  /* check Plan Cache and Query Cache parameters */
10127  if (PRM_GET_INT (max_plan_cache_entries_prm->value) == 0)
10128  {
10129  /* 0 means disable plan cache */
10130  (void) prm_set (max_plan_cache_entries_prm, "-1", false);
10131  }
10132 
10133 #if defined (WINDOWS)
10134  /* reset to default 'active mode' */
10135  (void) prm_set_default (ha_mode_prm);
10136 #endif
10137 
10138  if (PRM_GET_INT (ha_mode_prm->value) != HA_MODE_OFF)
10139  {
10140  int ha_check_disk_failure_interval_value;
10141  int ha_copy_log_timeout_value;
10142 
10143  ha_check_disk_failure_interval_value = PRM_GET_INT (ha_check_disk_failure_interval_prm->value);
10144  ha_copy_log_timeout_value = PRM_GET_INT (ha_copy_log_timeout_prm->value);
10145  if (ha_copy_log_timeout_value == -1)
10146  {
10147  prm_set (ha_check_disk_failure_interval_prm, "0", false);
10148  }
10149  else if (ha_check_disk_failure_interval_value - ha_copy_log_timeout_value <
10150  HB_MIN_DIFF_CHECK_DISK_FAILURE_INTERVAL_IN_SECS)
10151  {
10152  ha_check_disk_failure_interval_value =
10153  ha_copy_log_timeout_value + HB_MIN_DIFF_CHECK_DISK_FAILURE_INTERVAL_IN_SECS;
10154  sprintf (newval, "%ds", ha_check_disk_failure_interval_value);
10155  prm_set (ha_check_disk_failure_interval_prm, newval, false);
10156  }
10157  }
10158 
10159  /* disable them temporarily */
10160 
10161  if (ha_node_list_prm == NULL || PRM_DEFAULT_VAL_USED (*ha_node_list_prm->dynamic_flag))
10162  {
10163  if (GETHOSTNAME (host_name, sizeof (host_name)))
10164  {
10165  strncpy (host_name, "localhost", sizeof (host_name) - 1);
10166  }
10167 
10168  snprintf (newval, sizeof (newval) - 1, "%s@%s", host_name, host_name);
10169  prm_set (ha_node_list_prm, newval, false);
10170  }
10171 
10172  assert (ha_mode_prm != NULL);
10173 
10174  if (PRM_GET_BOOL (test_mode_prm->value) == true)
10175  {
10176  tz_leap_second_support_prm->static_flag |= PRM_FOR_QRY_STRING;
10177  }
10178 
10179  return;
10180 }
10181 #endif /* CS_MODE */

10219 /*
10220  * prm_set_compound - Sets the values of various system parameters based on
10221  * the value of a "compound" parameter.
10222  * return: none
10223  * param(in): the compound parameter whose value has changed
10224  * compound_param_values(in): an array of arrays that indicate the name of
10225  * the parameter to change and its new value.
10226  * NULL indicates resetting the parameter to its
10227  * default. The name of the parameter is the last
10228  * element of the array, 1 past the upper limit
10229  * of the compound parameter.
10230  * values_count(in): the number of elements in the compound_param_values
10231  * array
10232  */
10233 static void
10234 prm_set_compound (SYSPRM_PARAM * param, const char **compound_param_values[], const int values_count, bool set_flag)
10235 {
10236  int i = 0;
10237  const int param_value = *(int *) param->value;
10238  const int param_upper_limit = *(int *) param->upper_limit;
10239 
10240  assert (PRM_IS_INTEGER (param) || PRM_IS_KEYWORD (param));
10241  assert (0 == *(int *) param->lower_limit);
10242  assert (param_value <= param_upper_limit);
10243 
10244  for (i = 0; i < values_count; ++i)
10245  {
10246  const char *compound_param_name = compound_param_values[i][param_upper_limit + 1];
10247  const char *compound_param_value = compound_param_values[i][param_value];
10248 
10249  assert (compound_param_name != NULL);
10250 
10251  if (compound_param_value == NULL)
10252  {
10253  prm_set_default (prm_find (compound_param_name, NULL));
10254  }
10255  else
10256  {
10257  prm_set (prm_find (compound_param_name, NULL), compound_param_value, set_flag);
10258  }
10259  }
10260 }
10261 
10262 /*
10263  * prm_get_next_param_value - get next param=value token from a string
10264  * containing a "param1=val1;param2=val2..." list
10265  * return: NO_ERROR or error code if data format is incorrect
10266  * data (in): the string containing the list
10267  * prm (out): parameter name
10268  * val (out): parameter value
10269  */
10270 static int
10271 prm_get_next_param_value (char **data, char **prm, char **val)
10272 {
10273  char *p = *data;
10274  char *name = NULL;
10275  char *value = NULL;
10276  int err = PRM_ERR_NO_ERROR;
10277 
10278  while (char_isspace (*p))
10279  {
10280  p++;
10281  }
10282 
10283  if (*p == '\0')
10284  {
10285  /* reached the end of the list */
10286  err = PRM_ERR_NO_ERROR;
10287  goto cleanup;
10288  }
10289 
10290  name = p;
10291  while (*p && !char_isspace (*p) && *p != '=')
10292  {
10293  p++;
10294  }
10295 
10296  if (*p == '\0')
10297  {
10298  err = PRM_ERR_BAD_VALUE;
10299  goto cleanup;
10300  }
10301  else if (*p == '=')
10302  {
10303  *p++ = '\0';
10304  }
10305  else
10306  {
10307  *p++ = '\0';
10308  while (char_isspace (*p))
10309  {
10310  p++;
10311  }
10312  if (*p == '=')
10313  {
10314  p++;
10315  }
10316  }
10317 
10318  while (char_isspace (*p))
10319  {
10320  p++;
10321  }
10322  if (*p == '\0')
10323  {
10324  err = PRM_ERR_NO_ERROR;
10325  goto cleanup;
10326  }
10327 
10328  value = p;
10329 
10330  if (*p == '"' || *p == '\'')
10331  {
10332  char *t, delim;
10333 
10334  delim = *p++;
10335  value = t = p;
10336  while (*t && *t != delim)
10337  {
10338  if (*t == '\\')
10339  {
10340  t++;
10341  }
10342  *p++ = *t++;
10343  }
10344  if (*t != delim)
10345  {
10346  err = PRM_ERR_BAD_STRING;
10347  goto cleanup;
10348  }
10349  }
10350  else
10351  {
10352  while (*p && !char_isspace (*p) && *p != ';')
10353  {
10354  p++;
10355  }
10356  }
10357 
10358  if (*p)
10359  {
10360  *p++ = '\0';
10361  while (char_isspace (*p))
10362  {
10363  p++;
10364  }
10365  if (*p == ';')
10366  {
10367  p++;
10368  }
10369  }
10370 
10371  *data = p;
10372  *val = value;
10373  *prm = name;
10374 
10375  return err;
10376 
10377 cleanup:
10378  *prm = NULL;
10379  *val = NULL;
10380  *data = NULL;
10381 
10382  return err;
10383 }

10400  * prm_get_value () - returns a pointer to the value of a system parameter
10401  *
10402  * return : pointer to value
10403  * prm_id (in) : parameter id
10404  *
10405  * NOTE: for session parameters, in server mode, the value stored in
10406  * conn_entry->session_parameters is returned instead of the value
10407  * from prm_Def array.

10410 prm_get_value (PARAM_ID prm_id)

10427

10429 #else /* SERVER_MODE */

10431

10433 #endif /* SERVER_MODE */
10434 }

10658 /*
10659  * sysprm_find_err_in_integer_list () - function that searches a error_code in an
10660  * integer list
10661  *
10662  * return : true if error_code is found, false otherwise
10663  * prm_id (in) : id of the system parameter that contains an integer list
10664  * error_code (in) : error_code to look for
10665  */
10666 bool
10667 sysprm_find_err_in_integer_list (PARAM_ID prm_id, int error_code)
10668 {
10669  int i;
10670  int *integer_list = prm_get_integer_list_value (prm_id);
10671 
10672  if (integer_list == NULL)
10673  {
10674  return false;
10675  }
10676 
10677  for (i = 1; i <= integer_list[0]; i++)
10678  {
10679  if (integer_list[i] == error_code || integer_list[i] == -error_code)
10680  {
10681  return true;
10682  }
10683  }
10684  return false;
10685 }
10686 
10687 /*
10688  * sysprm_find_fi_code_in_integer_list () - function that searches a FI_TEST_CODE in an
10689  * integer list
10690  *
10691  * return : true if FI_TEST_CODE is found, false otherwise
10692  * prm_id (in) : id of the system parameter that contains an integer list
10693  * fi_code (in) : FI_TEST_CODE to look for
10694  */
10695 bool
10696 sysprm_find_fi_code_in_integer_list (PARAM_ID prm_id, int fi_code)
10697 {
10698  int i;
10699  int *integer_list = prm_get_integer_list_value (prm_id);
10700 
10701  if (integer_list == NULL)
10702  {
10703  return false;
10704  }
10705 
10706  for (i = 1; i <= integer_list[0]; i++)
10707  {
10708  if (integer_list[i] == fi_code)
10709  {
10710  return true;
10711  }
10712  }
10713  return false;
10714 }

10716 /*
10717  * sysprm_update_flag_different () - updates the PRM_DIFFERENT bit in flag.
10718  *
10719  * return : void
10720  * prm (in) : system parameter to update
10721  *
10722  * NOTE: Should be called whenever a system parameter changes value.
10723  * This only affects parameters on client (there is no use for this flag
10724  * on server side) that are also flagged with PRM_FOR_QRY_STRING.
10725  */
10726 static void
10727 sysprm_update_flag_different (SYSPRM_PARAM * prm)
10728 {
10729 #if defined (CS_MODE)
10730  if (!PRM_IS_FOR_QRY_STRING (prm->static_flag) && !PRM_IS_FOR_HA_CONTEXT (prm->static_flag))
10731  {
10732  /* nothing to do */
10733  return;
10734  }
10735 
10736  /* compare current value with default value and update PRM_DIFFERENT bit */
10737  if (sysprm_compare_values (prm->value, prm->default_value, prm->datatype) != 0)
10738  {
10739  PRM_SET_BIT (PRM_DIFFERENT, *prm->dynamic_flag);
10740  }
10741  else
10742  {
10743  PRM_CLEAR_BIT (PRM_DIFFERENT, *prm->dynamic_flag);
10744  }
10745 #endif /* CS_MODE */
10746 }
10747 
10748 /*
10749  * sysprm_update_flag_allocated () - update PRM_ALLOCATED flag. If value is
10750  * NULL, the bit is cleared, if not, the bit
10751  * is set.
10752  *
10753  * return : void.
10754  * prm (in) : system parameter.
10755  */
10756 static void
10757 sysprm_update_flag_allocated (SYSPRM_PARAM * prm)
10758 {
10759  bool allocated;
10760  switch (prm->datatype)
10761  {
10762  case PRM_STRING:
10763  allocated = PRM_GET_STRING (prm->value) != NULL;
10764  break;
10765 
10766  case PRM_INTEGER_LIST:
10767  allocated = PRM_GET_INTEGER_LIST (prm->value) != NULL;
10768  break;
10769 
10770  default:
10771  allocated = false;
10772  break;
10773  }
10774 
10775  if (allocated)
10776  {
10777  PRM_SET_BIT (PRM_ALLOCATED, *prm->dynamic_flag);
10778  }
10779  else
10780  {
10781  PRM_CLEAR_BIT (PRM_ALLOCATED, *prm->dynamic_flag);
10782  }
10783 }
10784 
10785 /*
10786  * sysprm_update_session_prm_flag_allocated () - update PRM_ALLOCATED flag for
10787  * session parameters. If the
10788  * value is null, the bit is
10789  * cleared, if not, the bit is
10790  * set.
10791  *
10792  * return : void
10793  * prm (in) : session parameter
10794  */
10795 static void
10796 sysprm_update_session_prm_flag_allocated (SESSION_PARAM * prm)
10797 {
10798  bool allocated;
10799  switch (prm->datatype)
10800  {
10801  case PRM_STRING:
10802  allocated = prm->value.str != NULL;
10803  break;
10804 
10805  case PRM_INTEGER_LIST:
10806  allocated = prm->value.integer_list != NULL;
10807  break;
10808 
10809  default:
10810  allocated = false;
10811  break;
10812  }
10813 
10814  if (allocated)
10815  {
10816  PRM_SET_BIT (PRM_ALLOCATED, prm->flag);
10817  }
10818  else
10819  {
10820  PRM_CLEAR_BIT (PRM_ALLOCATED, prm->flag);
10821  }
10822 }
10823 
10824 /*
10825  * sysprm_clear_sysprm_value () - Clears a SYSPRM_VALUE.
10826  *
10827  * return : void.
10828  * value (in) : value that needs cleared.
10829  * datatype (in) : data type for value.
10830  */
10831 static void
10832 sysprm_clear_sysprm_value (SYSPRM_VALUE * value, SYSPRM_DATATYPE datatype)
10833 {
10834  switch (datatype)
10835  {
10836  case PRM_STRING:
10837  free_and_init (value->str);
10838  break;
10839 
10840  case PRM_INTEGER_LIST:
10841  free_and_init (value->integer_list);
10842  break;
10843 
10844  default:
10845  /* do nothing */
10846  break;
10847  }
10848 }
10849 
10850 /*
10851  * sysprm_alloc_session_parameters () - allocates memory for session
10852  * parameters array
10853  *
10854  * return : NULL or pointer to array of session parameters
10855  */
10856 static SESSION_PARAM *
10857 sysprm_alloc_session_parameters (void)
10858 {
10859  SESSION_PARAM *result = NULL;
10860  size_t size;
10861 
10862  if (NUM_SESSION_PRM == 0)
10863  {
10864  return NULL;
10865  }
10866  size = NUM_SESSION_PRM * sizeof (SESSION_PARAM);
10867  result = (SESSION_PARAM *) malloc (size);
10868  if (result == NULL)
10869  {
10870  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, size);
10871  return NULL;
10872  }
10873  memset (result, 0, size);
10874  return result;
10875 }
10876 
10877 /*
10878  * sysprm_free_session_parameters () - free session parameter array
10879  *
10880  * return : void
10881  * session_parameters_ptr (in) : pointer to session parameter array
10882  */
10883 void
10884 sysprm_free_session_parameters (SESSION_PARAM ** session_parameters_ptr)
10885 {
10886  int i = 0;
10887  SESSION_PARAM *sprm = NULL;
10888 
10889  assert (session_parameters_ptr != NULL);
10890 
10891  if (*session_parameters_ptr == NULL)
10892  {
10893  return;
10894  }
10895 
10896  for (i = 0; i < NUM_SESSION_PRM; i++)
10897  {
10898  sprm = &((*session_parameters_ptr)[i]);
10899  sysprm_clear_sysprm_value (&sprm->value, (SYSPRM_DATATYPE) sprm->datatype);
10900  }
10901 
10902  free_and_init (*session_parameters_ptr);
10903 }
10904 
10905 /*
10906  * sysprm_pack_sysprm_value () - Packs a sysprm_value.
10907  *
10908  * return : pointer after the packed value.
10909  * ptr (in) : pointer to position where the value should be packed.
10910  * value (in) : sysprm_value to be packed.
10911  * datatype (in) : value data type.
10912  */
10913 static char *
10914 sysprm_pack_sysprm_value (char *ptr, SYSPRM_VALUE value, SYSPRM_DATATYPE datatype)
10915 {
10916  if (ptr == NULL)
10917  {
10918  return NULL;
10919  }
10920 
10921  ASSERT_ALIGN (ptr, INT_ALIGNMENT);
10922 
10923  switch (datatype)
10924  {
10925  case PRM_INTEGER:
10926  case PRM_KEYWORD:
10927  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, value.i);
10928  break;
10929 
10930  case PRM_BOOLEAN:
10931  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, value.b);
10932  break;
10933 
10934  case PRM_FLOAT:
10935  ptr = or_pack_float (ptr, value.f);
10936  break;
10937 
10938  case PRM_STRING:
10939  ptr = or_pack_string (ptr, value.str);
10940  break;
10941 
10942  case PRM_INTEGER_LIST:
10943  if (value.integer_list != NULL)
10944  {
10945  int i;
10946  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, value.integer_list[0]);
10947  for (i = 1; i <= value.integer_list[0]; i++)
10948  {
10949  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, value.integer_list[i]);
10950  }
10951  }
10952  else
10953  {
10954  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, -1);
10955  }
10956  break;
10957 
10958  case PRM_BIGINT:
10959  ptr = or_pack_int64 (ptr, value.bi);
10960  break;
10961  default:
10962  assert_release (0);
10963  break;
10964  }
10965 
10966  return ptr;
10967 }
10968 
10969 /*
10970  * sysprm_packed_sysprm_value_length () - size of packed sysprm_value.
10971  *
10972  * return : size of packed sysprm_value.
10973  * value (in) : sysprm_value.
10974  * datatype (in) : value data type.
10975  * offset (in) : offset to pointer where sysprm_value will be packed
10976  * (required for PRM_BIGINT data type)
10977  */
10978 static int
10979 sysprm_packed_sysprm_value_length (SYSPRM_VALUE value, SYSPRM_DATATYPE datatype, int offset)
10980 {
10981  switch (datatype)
10982  {
10983  case PRM_INTEGER:
10984  case PRM_KEYWORD:
10985  case PRM_BOOLEAN:
10986  return OR_INT_SIZE;
10987 
10988  case PRM_FLOAT:
10989  return OR_FLOAT_SIZE;
10990 
10991  case PRM_STRING:
10992  return or_packed_string_length (value.str, NULL);
10993 
10994  case PRM_INTEGER_LIST:
10995  if (value.integer_list != NULL)
10996  {
10997  return OR_INT_SIZE * (value.integer_list[0] + 1);
10998  }
10999  else
11000  {
11001  return OR_INT_SIZE;
11002  }
11003 
11004  case PRM_BIGINT:
11005  /* pointer will be aligned to MAX_ALIGNMENT */
11006  return DB_ALIGN (offset, MAX_ALIGNMENT) - offset + OR_INT64_SIZE;
11007 
11008  default:
11009  return 0;
11010  }
11011 }
11012 
11013 /*
11014  * sysprm_unpack_sysprm_value () - unpacks a sysprm_value.
11015  *
11016  * return : pointer after the unpacked sysprm_value.
11017  * ptr (in) : pointer to the position where sysprm_value is packed.
11018  * value (out) : pointer to unpacked sysprm_value.
11019  * datatype (in) : value data type.
11020  */
11021 static char *
11022 sysprm_unpack_sysprm_value (char *ptr, SYSPRM_VALUE * value, SYSPRM_DATATYPE datatype)
11023 {
11024  assert (value != NULL);
11025 
11026  if (ptr == NULL)
11027  {
11028  return NULL;
11029  }
11030 
11031  ASSERT_ALIGN (ptr, INT_ALIGNMENT);
11032 
11033  switch (datatype)
11034  {
11035  case PRM_INTEGER:
11036  case PRM_KEYWORD:
11037  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &value->i);
11038  break;
11039 
11040  case PRM_BOOLEAN:
11041  {
11042  int temp;
11043  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &temp);
11044  value->b = temp;
11045  }
11046  break;
11047 
11048  case PRM_FLOAT:
11049  ptr = or_unpack_float (ptr, &value->f);
11050  break;
11051 
11052  case PRM_STRING:
11053  {
11054  char *str = NULL;
11055  ptr = or_unpack_string_nocopy (ptr, &str);
11056  if (str != NULL)
11057  {
11058  value->str = strdup (str);
11059  if (value->str == NULL)
11060  {
11061  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, (size_t) (strlen (str) + 1));
11062  return NULL;
11063  }
11064  }
11065  else
11066  {
11067  value->str = NULL;
11068  }
11069  }
11070  break;
11071 
11072  case PRM_INTEGER_LIST:
11073  {
11074  int temp, i;
11075  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &temp);
11076  if (temp == -1)
11077  {
11078  value->integer_list = NULL;
11079  }
11080  else
11081  {
11082  value->integer_list = (int *) malloc ((temp + 1) * OR_INT_SIZE);
11083  if (value->integer_list == NULL)
11084  {
11085  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1,
11086  (size_t) ((temp + 1) * OR_INT_SIZE));
11087  return NULL;
11088  }
11089  else
11090  {
11091  value->integer_list[0] = temp;
11092  for (i = 1; i <= temp; i++)
11093  {
11094  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &value->integer_list[i]);
11095  }
11096  }
11097  }
11098  }
11099  break;
11100 
11101  case PRM_BIGINT:
11102  {
11103  INT64 size;
11104  ptr = or_unpack_int64 (ptr, &size);
11105  value->bi = (UINT64) size;
11106  }
11107  break;
11108 
11109  default:
11110  break;
11111  }
11112 
11113  return ptr;
11114 }
11115 
11116 /*
11117  * sysprm_pack_session_parameters () - packs the array of session parameters
11118  *
11119  * return : new position pointer after packing
11120  * ptr (in) : pointer to the position where the packing starts
11121  * session_parameters (in) : array of session parameters
11122  */
11123 char *
11124 sysprm_pack_session_parameters (char *ptr, SESSION_PARAM * session_parameters)
11125 {
11126  SESSION_PARAM *prm = NULL;
11127  int i = 0;
11128 
11129  if (ptr == NULL)
11130  {
11131  return NULL;
11132  }
11133 
11134  ASSERT_ALIGN (ptr, INT_ALIGNMENT);
11135 
11136  for (i = 0; i < NUM_SESSION_PRM; i++)
11137  {
11138  prm = &session_parameters[i];
11139 
11140  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, prm->prm_id);
11141  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, prm->flag);
11142  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, prm->datatype);
11143  ptr = sysprm_pack_sysprm_value (ptr, prm->value, (SYSPRM_DATATYPE) prm->datatype);
11144  }
11145 
11146  return ptr;
11147 }
11148 
11149 /*
11150  * sysprm_packed_session_parameters_length () - returns the length needed to
11151  * pack an array of session
11152  * parameters
11153  *
11154  * return : size of packed data
11155  * session_parameters (in) : array of session parameters
11156  * offset (in) : the offset to packed session parameters
11157  */
11158 int
11159 sysprm_packed_session_parameters_length (SESSION_PARAM * session_parameters, int offset)
11160 {
11161  SESSION_PARAM *prm = NULL;
11162  int size = 0, i = 0;
11163 
11164  for (i = 0; i < NUM_SESSION_PRM; i++)
11165  {
11166  prm = &session_parameters[i];
11167  size += OR_INT_SIZE; /* prm_id */
11168  size += OR_INT_SIZE; /* flag */
11169  size += OR_INT_SIZE; /* datatype */
11170  size += /* value */
11171  sysprm_packed_sysprm_value_length (session_parameters[i].value, (SYSPRM_DATATYPE) prm->datatype, size + offset);
11172  }
11173 
11174  return size;
11175 }
11176 
11177 /*
11178  * sysprm_unpack_session_parameters () - unpacks an array of session parameters
11179  * from buffer
11180  *
11181  * return : new pointer position after unpacking
11182  * ptr (in) : pointer to position where unpacking starts
11183  * session_parameters_ptr (out) : pointer to the unpacked list of session
11184  * parameters
11185  */
11186 char *
11187 sysprm_unpack_session_parameters (char *ptr, SESSION_PARAM ** session_parameters_ptr)
11188 {
11189  SESSION_PARAM *prm, *session_params = NULL;
11190  int prm_index, tmp;
11191 
11192  assert (session_parameters_ptr != NULL);
11193  *session_parameters_ptr = NULL;
11194 
11195  if (ptr == NULL)
11196  {
11197  return NULL;
11198  }
11199 
11200  ASSERT_ALIGN (ptr, INT_ALIGNMENT);
11201 
11202  session_params = sysprm_alloc_session_parameters ();
11203  if (session_params == NULL)
11204  {
11205  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, sizeof (SESSION_PARAM));
11206  goto error;
11207  }
11208 
11209  for (prm_index = 0; prm_index < NUM_SESSION_PRM; prm_index++)
11210  {
11211  int flag;
11212 
11213  prm = &session_params[prm_index];
11214 
11215  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &tmp);
11216  prm->prm_id = (PARAM_ID) tmp;
11217 
11218  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &flag);
11219  prm->flag = (unsigned int) flag;
11220 
11221  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &prm->datatype);
11222 
11223  ptr = sysprm_unpack_sysprm_value (ptr, &prm->value, (SYSPRM_DATATYPE) prm->datatype);
11224  if (ptr == NULL)
11225  {
11226  /* error unpacking value */
11227  goto error;
11228  }
11229  sysprm_update_session_prm_flag_allocated (prm);
11230  }
11231 
11232  *session_parameters_ptr = session_params;
11233  return ptr;
11234 
11235 error:
11236  /* clean up */
11237  sysprm_free_session_parameters (&session_params);
11238  return NULL;
11239 }
11240 
11241 /*
11242  * sysprm_pack_assign_values () - packs a list of SYSPRM_ASSIGN_VALUEs.
11243  *
11244  * return : pointer after the packed list.
11245  * ptr (in) : pointer to position where the list should be packed.
11246  * assign_values (in) : list of sysprm_assign_values.
11247  */
11248 char *
11249 sysprm_pack_assign_values (char *ptr, const SYSPRM_ASSIGN_VALUE * assign_values)
11250 {
11251  char *old_ptr = ptr;
11252  int count;
11253 
11254  ASSERT_ALIGN (ptr, INT_ALIGNMENT);
11255 
11256  /* skip one int -> size of assign_values */
11257  ptr += OR_INT_SIZE;
11258 
11259  for (count = 0; assign_values != NULL; assign_values = assign_values->next, count++)
11260  {
11261  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, assign_values->prm_id);
11262  ptr = sysprm_pack_sysprm_value (ptr, assign_values->value, GET_PRM_DATATYPE (assign_values->prm_id));
11263  }
11264 
11265  OR_PUT_INT (old_ptr, count);
11266  return ptr;
11267 }
11268 
11269 /*
11270  * sysprm_packed_assign_values_length () - size of packed list of
11271  * sysprm_assing_values.
11272  *
11273  * return : size of packed list of sysprm_assing_values.
11274  * assign_values (in) : list of sysprm_assing_values.
11275  * offset (in) : offset to pointer where assign values will be packed.
11276  */
11277 int
11278 sysprm_packed_assign_values_length (const SYSPRM_ASSIGN_VALUE * assign_values, int offset)
11279 {
11280  int size = 0;
11281 
11282  size += OR_INT_SIZE; /* size of assign_values list */
11283 
11284  for (; assign_values != NULL; assign_values = assign_values->next)
11285  {
11286  size += OR_INT_SIZE; /* prm_id */
11287  size +=
11288  sysprm_packed_sysprm_value_length (assign_values->value, GET_PRM_DATATYPE (assign_values->prm_id),
11289  size + offset);
11290  }
11291 
11292  return size;
11293 }
11294 
11295 /*
11296  * sysprm_unpack_assign_values () - Unpacks a list of sysprm_assign_values.
11297  *
11298  * return : pointer after unpacking sysprm_assing_values.
11299  * ptr (in) : pointer to the position where
11300  * sysprm_assing_values are packed.
11301  * assign_values_ptr (out) : pointer to the unpacked list of
11302  * sysprm_assing_values.
11303  */
11304 char *
11305 sysprm_unpack_assign_values (char *ptr, SYSPRM_ASSIGN_VALUE ** assign_values_ptr)
11306 {
11307  SYSPRM_ASSIGN_VALUE *assign_values = NULL, *last_assign_val = NULL;
11308  SYSPRM_ASSIGN_VALUE *assign_val = NULL;
11309  int i = 0, count = 0, tmp;
11310 
11311  assert (assign_values_ptr != NULL);
11312  *assign_values_ptr = NULL;
11313 
11314  if (ptr == NULL)
11315  {
11316  return NULL;
11317  }
11318 
11319  ASSERT_ALIGN (ptr, INT_ALIGNMENT);
11320 
11321  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &count);
11322  if (count <= 0)
11323  {
11324  return ptr;
11325  }
11326 
11327  for (i = 0; i < count; i++)
11328  {
11329  assign_val = (SYSPRM_ASSIGN_VALUE *) malloc (sizeof (SYSPRM_ASSIGN_VALUE));
11330  if (assign_val == NULL)
11331  {
11332  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, sizeof (SYSPRM_ASSIGN_VALUE));
11333  goto error;
11334  }
11335 
11336  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &tmp);
11337  assign_val->prm_id = (PARAM_ID) tmp;
11338 
11339  ptr = sysprm_unpack_sysprm_value (ptr, &assign_val->value, GET_PRM_DATATYPE (assign_val->prm_id));
11340  if (ptr == NULL)
11341  {
11342  free_and_init (assign_val);
11343  goto error;
11344  }
11345  assign_val->next = NULL;
11346  if (assign_values != NULL)
11347  {
11348  last_assign_val->next = assign_val;
11349  last_assign_val = assign_val;
11350  }
11351  else
11352  {
11353  assign_values = last_assign_val = assign_val;
11354  }
11355  }
11356 
11357  *assign_values_ptr = assign_values;
11358  return ptr;
11359 
11360 error:
11361  sysprm_free_assign_values (&assign_values);
11362  return NULL;
11363 }
11364 
11365 /*
11366  * sysprm_free_assign_values () - free a list of sysprm_assign_values.
11367  *
11368  * return : void
11369  * assign_values_ptr (in/out) : pointer to list to free.
11370  */
11371 void
11372 sysprm_free_assign_values (SYSPRM_ASSIGN_VALUE ** assign_values_ptr)
11373 {
11374  SYSPRM_ASSIGN_VALUE *assignment = NULL, *save_next = NULL;
11375 
11376  if (assign_values_ptr == NULL || *assign_values_ptr == NULL)
11377  {
11378  return;
11379  }
11380  assignment = *assign_values_ptr;
11381 
11382  while (assignment != NULL)
11383  {
11384  save_next = assignment->next;
11385  sysprm_clear_sysprm_value (&assignment->value, GET_PRM_DATATYPE (assignment->prm_id));
11386  free_and_init (assignment);
11387  assignment = save_next;
11388  }
11389 
11390  *assign_values_ptr = NULL;
11391 }
11392 
11393 /*
11394  * sysprm_get_id () - returns the id for a system parameter
11395  *
11396  * return : id
11397  * prm(in) : address for system parameter
11398  */
11399 static PARAM_ID
11400 sysprm_get_id (const SYSPRM_PARAM * prm)
11401 {
11402  int id = (int) (prm - prm_Def);
11403 
11404  assert (id >= PRM_FIRST_ID && id <= PRM_LAST_ID);
11405 
11406  return (PARAM_ID) id;
11407 }
11408 
11409 #if defined (SERVER_MODE)
11410 /*
11411  * update_session_state_from_sys_params () - Updates the session state members
11412  * from session system parameters
11413  *
11414  * return : void
11415  * thread_p (in) : thread entry
11416  * session_params (in) : pointer to session parameters vector
11417  *
11418  */
11419 static void
11420 update_session_state_from_sys_params (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, SESSION_PARAM * session_params)
11421 {
11422  TZ_REGION *session_tz_region;
11423  int i;
11424 
11425  session_tz_region = session_get_session_tz_region (thread_p);
11426  if (session_tz_region != NULL)
11427  {
11428  for (i = 0; i < NUM_SESSION_PRM; i++)
11429  {
11430  if (session_params[i].prm_id == PRM_ID_TIMEZONE)
11431  {
11432  tz_str_to_region (session_params[i].value.str, strlen (session_params[i].value.str), session_tz_region);
11433  break;
11434  }
11435  }
11436  }
11437 }
11438 
11439 /*
11440  * sysprm_session_init_session_parameters () - adds array of session
11441  * parameters to session state and
11442  * connection entry.
11443  *
11444  * return : NO_ERROR or error_code
11445  * session_parameters_ptr (in/out) : array of session parameters sent by
11446  * client while registering to server
11447  * found_session_parameters (out) : true if session parameters were found in
11448  * session state, false otherwise
11449  *
11450  * NOTE: If the session state already has session parameters, the client must
11451  * have reconnected. The values stored in session state will be used
11452  * instead of the values sent by client (this way the client recovers
11453  * the session parameters changed before disconnecting).
11454  */
11455 int
11456 sysprm_session_init_session_parameters (SESSION_PARAM ** session_parameters_ptr, int *found_session_parameters)
11457 {
11458  THREAD_ENTRY *thread_p = thread_get_thread_entry_info ();
11459  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
11460  SESSION_PARAM *session_params = NULL;
11461 
11462  assert (found_session_parameters != NULL);
11463  *found_session_parameters = 0;
11464 
11465  /* first check if there is a list in session state */
11466  error_code = session_get_session_parameters (thread_p, &session_params);
11467  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
11468  {
11469  return error_code;
11470  }
11471 
11472  if (session_params == NULL)
11473  {
11474  /* set the parameter values sent by client to session state */
11475  session_params = *session_parameters_ptr;
11476  error_code = session_set_session_parameters (thread_p, session_params);
11477  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
11478  {
11479  return error_code;
11480  }
11481  update_session_state_from_sys_params (thread_p, session_params);
11482  }
11483  else
11484  {
11485  /* use the values stored in session state and free the session parameters received from client */
11486  sysprm_free_session_parameters (session_parameters_ptr);
11487  *session_parameters_ptr = session_params;
11488  *found_session_parameters = 1;
11489  }
11490 
11491  return NO_ERROR;
11492 }
11493 
11494 /*
11495  * sysprm_set_session_parameter_value - set a new value for the session
11496  * parameter identified by id.
11497  * return : PRM_ERR_NO_ERROR or error_code
11498  * session_parameter (in) : session parameter to set the value of
11499  * id (in) : id for the session parameter that needs changed
11500  * value (in) : new value
11501  */
11502 static SYSPRM_ERR
11503 sysprm_set_session_parameter_value (SESSION_PARAM * session_parameter, int id, SYSPRM_VALUE value)
11504 {
11505  switch (session_parameter->datatype)
11506  {
11507  case PRM_INTEGER:
11508  case PRM_KEYWORD:
11509  session_parameter->value.i = value.i;
11510  break;
11511 
11512  case PRM_FLOAT:
11513  session_parameter->value.f = value.f;
11514  break;
11515 
11516  case PRM_BOOLEAN:
11517  session_parameter->value.b = value.b;
11518  break;
11519 
11520  case PRM_STRING:
11521  if (PRM_IS_ALLOCATED (session_parameter->flag))
11522  {
11523  free_and_init (session_parameter->value.str);
11524  PRM_CLEAR_BIT (PRM_ALLOCATED, session_parameter->flag);
11525  }
11526  session_parameter->value.str = value.str;
11527  if (session_parameter->value.str != NULL)
11528  {
11529  PRM_SET_BIT (PRM_ALLOCATED, session_parameter->flag);
11530  }
11531  break;
11532 
11533  case PRM_INTEGER_LIST:
11534  if (PRM_IS_ALLOCATED (session_parameter->flag))
11535  {
11536  free_and_init (session_parameter->value.integer_list);
11537  PRM_CLEAR_BIT (PRM_ALLOCATED, session_parameter->flag);
11538  }
11539  session_parameter->value.integer_list = value.integer_list;
11540  if (session_parameter->value.integer_list != NULL)
11541  {
11542  PRM_SET_BIT (PRM_ALLOCATED, session_parameter->flag);
11543  }
11544  break;
11545 
11546  case PRM_BIGINT:
11547  session_parameter->value.bi = value.bi;
11548  break;
11549  }
11550 
11551  return PRM_ERR_NO_ERROR;
11552 }

11607 /*
11608  * sysprm_compare_values () - compare two system parameter values
11609  *
11610  * return : comparison result (0 - equal, otherwise - different).
11611  * first_value (in) : pointer to first value
11612  * second_value (in) : pointer to second value
11613  * val_type (in) : datatype for values (make sure the values that are
11614  * compared have the same datatype)
11615  */
11616 static int
11617 sysprm_compare_values (void *first_value, void *second_value, unsigned int val_type)
11618 {
11619  switch (val_type)
11620  {
11621  case PRM_INTEGER:
11622  case PRM_KEYWORD:
11623  return (PRM_GET_INT (first_value) != PRM_GET_INT (second_value));
11624 
11625  case PRM_BOOLEAN:
11626  return (PRM_GET_BOOL (first_value) != PRM_GET_BOOL (second_value));
11627 
11628  case PRM_FLOAT:
11629  return (PRM_GET_FLOAT (first_value) != PRM_GET_FLOAT (second_value));
11630 
11631  case PRM_STRING:
11632  {
11633  char *first_str = PRM_GET_STRING (first_value);
11634  char *second_str = PRM_GET_STRING (second_value);
11635 
11636  if (first_str == NULL && second_str == NULL)
11637  {
11638  /* both values are null, return equal */
11639  return 0;
11640  }
11641 
11642  if (first_str == NULL || second_str == NULL)
11643  {
11644  /* only one is null, return different */
11645  return 1;
11646  }
11647 
11648  return intl_mbs_casecmp (first_str, second_str);
11649  }
11650 
11651  case PRM_BIGINT:
11652  return (PRM_GET_BIGINT (first_value) != PRM_GET_BIGINT (second_value));
11653 
11654  case PRM_INTEGER_LIST:
11655  {
11656  int i;
11657  int *first_int_list = PRM_GET_INTEGER_LIST (first_value);
11658  int *second_int_list = PRM_GET_INTEGER_LIST (second_value);
11659 
11660  if (first_int_list == NULL && second_int_list == NULL)
11661  {
11662  /* both values are null, return equal */
11663  return 0;
11664  }
11665 
11666  if (second_int_list == NULL || second_int_list == NULL)
11667  {
11668  /* only one value is null, return different */
11669  return 1;
11670  }
11671 
11672  if (first_int_list[0] != second_int_list[0])
11673  {
11674  /* different size for integer lists, return different */
11675  return 1;
11676  }
11677 
11678  for (i = 1; i <= second_int_list[0]; i++)
11679  {
11680  if (first_int_list[i] != second_int_list[i])
11681  {
11682  /* found a different integer, return different */
11683  return 0;
11684  }
11685  }
11686 
11687  /* all integers are equal, return equal */
11688  return 1;
11689  }
11690 
11691  default:
11692  assert (0);
11693  break;
11694  }
11695 
11696  return 0;
11697 }
11698 
11699 /*
11700  * sysprm_set_sysprm_value_from_parameter () - set the value of sysprm_value
11701  * from a system parameter.
11702  *
11703  * return : void.
11704  * prm_value (in) : sysprm_value.
11705  * prm (in) : system parameter.
11706  */
11707 static void
11708 sysprm_set_sysprm_value_from_parameter (SYSPRM_VALUE * prm_value, SYSPRM_PARAM * prm)
11709 {
11710  size_t size;
11711 
11712  switch (prm->datatype)
11713  {
11714  case PRM_INTEGER:
11715  case PRM_KEYWORD:
11716  prm_value->i = PRM_GET_INT (prm->value);
11717  break;
11718  case PRM_FLOAT:
11719  prm_value->f = PRM_GET_FLOAT (prm->value);
11720  break;
11721  case PRM_BOOLEAN:
11722  prm_value->b = PRM_GET_BOOL (prm->value);
11723  break;
11724  case PRM_BIGINT:
11725  prm_value->bi = PRM_GET_BIGINT (prm->value);
11726  break;
11727  case PRM_STRING:
11728  if (PRM_GET_STRING (prm->value) != NULL)
11729  {
11730  prm_value->str = strdup (PRM_GET_STRING (prm->value));
11731  if (prm_value->str == NULL)
11732  {
11733  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1,
11734  (size_t) (strlen (PRM_GET_STRING (prm->value)) + 1));
11735  }
11736  }
11737  else
11738  {
11739  prm_value->str = NULL;
11740  }
11741  break;
11742  case PRM_INTEGER_LIST:
11743  {
11744  int *integer_list = PRM_GET_INTEGER_LIST (prm->value);
11745  if (integer_list != NULL)
11746  {
11747  size = (integer_list[0] + 1) * sizeof (int);
11748  prm_value->integer_list = (int *) malloc (size);
11749  if (prm_value->integer_list == NULL)
11750  {
11751  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, size);
11752  }
11753  else
11754  {
11755  memcpy (prm_value->integer_list, integer_list, size);
11756  }
11757  }
11758  else
11759  {
11760  prm_value->integer_list = NULL;
11761  }
11762  break;
11763  }
11764  case PRM_NO_TYPE:
11765  break;
11766  default:
11767  assert_release (0);
11768  break;
11769  }
11770 }

11800 /*

11952  return NULL;

11967 /*
11968  * sysprm_init_intl_param () -
11969  *
11970  * return:
11971  */
11972 int
11973 sysprm_init_intl_param (void)
11974 {
11975  SYSPRM_PARAM *prm_date_lang;
11976  SYSPRM_PARAM *prm_number_lang;
11977  SYSPRM_PARAM *prm_intl_collation;
11978  SYSPRM_PARAM *prm_timezone;
11979  int error = NO_ERROR;
11980 
11981  prm_date_lang = prm_find (PRM_NAME_INTL_DATE_LANG, NULL);
11982  prm_number_lang = prm_find (PRM_NAME_INTL_NUMBER_LANG, NULL);
11983  prm_intl_collation = prm_find (PRM_NAME_INTL_COLLATION, NULL);
11984  prm_timezone = prm_find (PRM_NAME_TIMEZONE, NULL);
11985 
11986  /* intl system parameters are session based and depend on system language; The language is read from DB (and client
11987  * from server), after the system parameters module was initialized and default values read from configuration file.
11988  * This function avoids to override any value already read from config. If no values are set from config, then this
11989  * function sets the values according to the default language. On client (CAS), we set the client copy of the value,
11990  * and also the cached session parameter value (which is the default starting value, when the existing CAS serves
11991  * another session) is intialized. */
11992 
11993  if (prm_date_lang != NULL && !PRM_IS_SET (*prm_date_lang->dynamic_flag))
11994  {
11995  prm_set (prm_date_lang, lang_get_Lang_name (), true);
11996 #if defined (CS_MODE)
11997  sysprm_update_cached_session_param_val (PRM_ID_INTL_DATE_LANG);
11998 #endif
11999  }
12000 
12001  if (prm_number_lang != NULL && !PRM_IS_SET (*prm_number_lang->dynamic_flag))
12002  {
12003  prm_set (prm_number_lang, lang_get_Lang_name (), true);
12004 #if defined (CS_MODE)
12005  sysprm_update_cached_session_param_val (PRM_ID_INTL_NUMBER_LANG);
12006 #endif
12007  }
12008 
12009  if (prm_intl_collation != NULL && !PRM_IS_SET (*prm_intl_collation->dynamic_flag))
12010  {
12011  prm_set (prm_intl_collation, lang_get_collation_name (LANG_GET_BINARY_COLLATION (LANG_SYS_CODESET)), true);
12012 #if defined (CS_MODE)
12013  sysprm_update_cached_session_param_val (PRM_ID_INTL_COLLATION);
12014 #endif
12015  }
12016 
12017  if (prm_timezone != NULL && !PRM_IS_SET (*prm_timezone->dynamic_flag))
12018  {
12019  prm_set (prm_timezone, prm_get_string_value (PRM_ID_SERVER_TIMEZONE), true);
12020 #if defined (CS_MODE)
12021  sysprm_update_cached_session_param_val (PRM_ID_TIMEZONE);
12022 #endif
12023  }
12024 
12025  return error;
12026 }
12027 #endif /* !SERVER_MODE */

12029 /*
12030  * sysprm_set_error () - sets an error for system parameter errors
12031  *
12032  * return : error code
12033  * rc (in) : SYSPRM_ERR error
12034  * data (in) : data to be printed with error
12035  */
12036 int
12037 sysprm_set_error (SYSPRM_ERR rc, const char *data)
12038 {
12039  int error;
12040 
12041  /* first check if error was already set */
12042  error = er_errid ();
12043  if (error != NO_ERROR)
12044  {
12045  /* already set */
12046  return error;
12047  }
12048 
12049  if (rc != PRM_ERR_NO_ERROR)
12050  {
12051  switch (rc)
12052  {
12053  case PRM_ERR_UNKNOWN_PARAM:
12054  case PRM_ERR_BAD_VALUE:
12055  case PRM_ERR_BAD_STRING:
12056  case PRM_ERR_BAD_RANGE:
12057  if (data)
12058  {
12059  error = ER_PRM_BAD_VALUE;
12060  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, error, 1, data);
12061  }
12062  else
12063  {
12064  error = ER_PRM_BAD_VALUE_NO_DATA;
12065  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, error, 0);
12066  }
12067  break;
12068  case PRM_ERR_CANNOT_CHANGE:
12069  case PRM_ERR_NOT_FOR_CLIENT:
12070  case PRM_ERR_NOT_FOR_SERVER:
12071  if (data)
12072  {
12073  error = ER_PRM_CANNOT_CHANGE;
12074  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, error, 1, data);
12075  }
12076  else
12077  {
12078  error = ER_PRM_CANNOT_CHANGE_NO_DATA;
12079  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, error, 0);
12080  }
12081  break;
12082  case PRM_ERR_NOT_SOLE_TRAN:
12083  error = ER_NOT_SOLE_TRAN;
12084  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, error, 0);
12085  break;
12086  case PRM_ERR_COMM_ERR:
12087  error = ER_NET_SERVER_COMM_ERROR;
12088  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, error, 1, "db_set_system_parameters");
12089  break;
12090  case PRM_ERR_NO_MEM_FOR_PRM:
12091  default:
12092  error = ER_GENERIC_ERROR;
12093  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, error, 0);
12094  break;
12095  }
12096  }
12097 
12098  return error;
12099 }

12112 #if defined (CS_MODE)
12113 /*
12114  * sysprm_update_cached_session_param_val () - updates value of a cached
12115  * session parameter
12116  * prm_id (in) : cached session system paramater id to update
12117  *
12118  * Note : cached session parameters (global cached_session_parameters) are
12119  * default value copies of the system parameters which can be changed
12120  * in a session context; this should be used only during init process
12121  * to alter the default initial value of system parameter for session.
12122  */
12123 static void
12124 sysprm_update_cached_session_param_val (const PARAM_ID prm_id)
12125 {
12126  SESSION_PARAM *cached_session_prm;
12127  SYSPRM_PARAM *sys_prm;
12128  int i;
12129 
12130  assert (NUM_SESSION_PRM > 0);
12131 
12132  sys_prm = GET_PRM (prm_id);
12133 
12134  for (i = 0; i < NUM_SESSION_PRM; i++)
12135  {
12136  cached_session_prm = &cached_session_parameters[i];
12137  if (cached_session_prm->prm_id != prm_id)
12138  {
12139  continue;
12140  }
12141 
12142  cached_session_prm->flag = *sys_prm->dynamic_flag;
12143  sysprm_set_sysprm_value_from_parameter (&cached_session_prm->value, sys_prm);
12144  sysprm_update_session_prm_flag_allocated (cached_session_prm);
12145  break;
12146  }
